title: Data Engineer
summary:
Are you looking for a supportive and collaborative workplace with great benefits and clear career development? You’ve come to the right place. 
Why choose Manulife? 
Competitive Salary packages and performance bonuses 
Day 1 HMO + FREE coverage for your dependents (inclusive of same-sex partners) 
Retirement savings benefit 
Rewarding culture that values wellness and well-being  
Performance Bonus 
Global network of industry experts 
Extensive training resources 
Job Description: 
We’re looking for a Data Engineer to design and develop data pipelines and ETL jobs using Big Data Technologies. Get the chance to work with our team of experts and with key business stakeholder to transform business data into projects with real-world impact. 
Have the skills and knowledge for the job? Learn more about the opening below! 
Key Responsibilities: 
Design and develop data pipelines and ETL jobs using Big Data Technologies based on functional/non-functional business requirements 
Design and implement Data Integration/Ingestion/Extraction solutions based on high level architecture design 
Identify, design, and implement process improvements and delivery optimizations 
Collaborate with Stakeholders, Business Analysts, and Data Architects to assist and translate business requirements to technical solutions 
Develop big data and analytic solutions leveraging new or existing technology to advance Manulife’s all lines of business 
Exploratory data analysis; Query and process on-premise or cloud-based data, provide reports, summarize, and visualize the data 
Design, upgrade, and implement new data workflows, automation, tools, and API integrations 
Perform POC on new integration patterns and solutions 
Write and maintain technical documentation 
Perform unit tests and system integration tests 
Executes updates, patches, and other activities required to maintain and enhance the operations of on-premise or cloud-based environments 
Qualifications: 
At least 2 years experience as Data Engineer, with focus on Big Data processing and/or relational databases 
At least 2 years experience working with Microsoft Azure Data Platform, specifically Azure SQL Database, Azure Data Factory, ADLS storage account 
Experienced with working on Structured, Semi-Structured, and Unstructured datasets 
Experienced with any of the Big Data tools and technologies: 
Hadoop, Spark, Hive, Sqoop, Kafka, Nifi 
Experienced with relational SQL and NoSQL databases: 
MSSQL, Postgres, HBase, (MongoDB is a plus)big data 
Experienced in creating data pipelines and in developing complex and optimized queries 
Experienced with Workflow Management Tools: Airflow, Crontab, CA Workload Automation 
Knowledgeable with CI/CD tools 
Experienced in any of the following programming/scripting languages: 
SQL, Python, Shell, Scala 
Basic knowledge of Data Visualization in any of the following tools: 
Tableau, PowerBI, QlikView/QlikSense 
Knowledgeable in using collaboration tools (eg., MS Teams, Skype, Confluence, JIRA, etc.) 
Experience with any SLDC Methodologies and familiarity with different Agile methodologies 
Select the "Smashfly > JobStreet API" option on Workday when asked how you heard about us.
Let's make every day better together. Learn about our opportunities at JOBS.MANULIFE.COM
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Parking, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Business (e.g. Shirts)

title: Data Engineer | Day Shift | Permanent WFH | Day 1 HMO
summary:
Join a Fashion Retail Revolution – Data Engineering for a Bright Future!
Experience a career that lets you be who you are and love what you do. As a Data Engineer at CottonOn Group PTY, you'll be part of something bigger, contributing to a revolution in fashion retail. Our commitment to providing the best customer experience every single time is at the heart of what we do. With a permanent work-from-home setup, you'll enjoy the ultimate work-life balance, giving you the freedom to shape your future while pursuing your personal dreams. Join us and step out of your comfort zone to unlock new possibilities in the world of data engineering. Build your future with us, where "You Belong Here," and make a positive difference every day.
Our client, your partner in creating global impact
Our client, CottonOn Group PTY, started as a simple idea in 1988, selling denim jackets from the boot of a Ford Bronco at a market in Geelong, Australia. What began as a humble venture has now evolved into one of Australia's largest global fashion groups. Nigel Austin, our founder, envisioned taking the Aussie Lifestyle to the world while Doing Good along the way. Customer obsession, great value, and quality have been our guiding principles since day one. Join our team and be part of a company that's all about making a positive difference in people's lives.
Who are we looking for?
Be part of our client’s team as a Data Engineer and play a pivotal role in designing, developing, and maintaining data pipelines using Microsoft Azure Data Factory. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to create efficient data solutions, implement data integration using Azure Synapse Analytics, and ensure optimal data storage and retrieval. You’ll also monitor and troubleshoot data pipelines, provide structured data for analysis, and uphold data security and compliance standards while staying updated with evolving data engineering trends.
Job Overview
Employment Type: Full-time
Shift: Day (7am to 4pm PH Time)
Work Setup: Permanent WFH
Drive success to the team as you:
Design, develop, and maintain data pipelines using Microsoft Azure Data Factory, ensuring efficient data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) processes.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand data requirements and translate them into effective data solutions.
Implement data integration solutions using Microsoft Synapse Analytics (formerly known as SQL Data Warehouse).
Optimize data storage and retrieval processes for performance and cost-effectiveness.
Monitor and troubleshoot data pipelines, addressing any issues promptly to minimize downtime.
Collaborate with analysts to provide them with clean, structured data for analysis and reporting.
Ensure data security, compliance, and governance best practices are followed.
Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and technologies in data engineering and contribute to the evolution of our data architecture.
What do you need to be part of the team?
3-5 years' experience in Data Engineering.
Experience with SSIS, SQL, ETL, Azure Data Engineer, and Power BI.
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field (or equivalent experience).
Proven experience working with Microsoft Azure services, particularly Azure Data Factory and Azure Synapse Analytics.
Strong proficiency in SQL, ETL processes, and data modeling.
Experience with data warehousing concepts and practices.
Proficiency in at least one programming language (e.g., Python, Java) for scripting and automation.
Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Familiarity with data governance, security, and compliance standards.
Experience engineering solutions for use in a Power BI environment.
Azure certifications (e.g., Microsoft Certified: Azure Data Engineer) are a plus.
Nice to have experience in programming languages (e.g., Python, Java) for scripting and automation.
Nice to have retail experience.
Why choose us?
Day 1 HMO coverage
Permanent work from home setup
Dayshift
Standard government and Emapta benefits
20 days annual leave
Career growth opportunities
Diverse and supportive work environment
Fun employee engagement activities
Who are we?
Discover a world of possibilities at Emapta, where your career takes flight in stability and growth. Join a team that thrives on camaraderie, supporting each other to achieve excellence together. Experience the satisfaction of being recognized for your contributions with competitive compensation packages that reflect your skills and commitment. Immerse yourself in a positive work culture that encourages collaboration, innovation, and personal development. We provide you with the platform for your success, empowering you to reach new heights in a supportive and inclusive environment.
With a wide roster of international clients from various industries and a proven track record of success, Emapta offers a stable foundation for your career. Team up with like-minded professionals who are passionate about making a meaningful impact through premium global opportunities at your fingertips. Apply now and create a better future with us.
#EmaptaExperience
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Loans, Sports (e.g. Gym), Emapta Academy, Smart casual, Morning / Mid / Night / Shifting

title: Data Engineer (Azure Data Platforms)
summary:
Emerson’s 132 years of history have been filled with achievements and challenges that have driven innovative thinking and bold transformations, molding us into the company we are today. By joining us as a Data Engineer, you will support Business Intelligence using the Azure suite of Analytics and Data platforms.
In this capacity, you will be focusing on the technical aspects and implementation of data gathering, integration, and model design, along with some report and dashboard creation. You will use Azure DevOps, Azure Synapse Analytics, and Power BI to create data models for strategic and self-service business intelligence. This gives you a very vital role in helping drive growth platforms and supporting operational pillars while striving for long-term value creation.
If this sounds like a perfect fit for you, apply now and join our team in Quezon City, Philippines! All roles are currently on a blended Work-From-Home arrangement, and company-provided IT assets are given on your first day. Enjoy our market-competitive pay, comprehensive benefits package, well-being programs, and career development opportunities.
In This Role, Your Responsibilities Will Be:
To implement robust data pipelines in Azure.
To build reusable and scalable data pipelines.
To develop and deploy new data platforms, data warehouses, data marts, etc.
To use Azure BI services to support strategic and self-service models and reports.
To work closely with the product owners and architects to develop Azure Data Platforms.
To practice internal standards for coding, project tracking, and documentation.
To integrate data from source systems/data lake into a data warehouse.
Who You Are:
You have a strong drive for results and exhibit passion and enthusiasm to get things done. You are a proactive self-starter with a high level of commitment to exceeding expectations. You can efficiently carry out tasks independently and generate accurate, high-quality reports. You can proficiently communicate ideas and influence both internal and external customers. You're interpersonally savvy and able to collaborate and efficiently work with people at any level in a multicultural environment.
For This Role, You Will Need:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or relevant courses.
3-5 years of relevant experience in Data Warehousing with cloud technologies and good software engineering principles.
Extensive experience connecting to various data sources and structures such as RDBMS, Data Lake, IoT, and Blob Storage.
Knowledge of PowerShell and strong practical experience with T-SQL or any variant from other RDBMS.
Working experience in Azure Services (Azure Data Factory and Azure Data Lake) and Azure DevOps paired with knowledge of Agile and/or Scrum methods of delivery.
Our Offer to You:
Make a difference with the work you do.
By joining Emerson, you'll be part of a versatile, dedicated team of motivated professionals who share a collective passion for progress and excellence.
At Emerson, we are committed to creating a global workplace that supports diversity and embraces inclusion. We attract, develop, and retain outstanding people in an inclusive environment where all employees can reach their greatest potential.
Join us and be part of a proud and thriving organization that values its people. Enjoy our market-competitive pay and benefits package, including food and transportation allowances, comprehensive insurance coverage, retirement benefits, and more. We invest in your growth with career development programs and reward your achievements through merit-based increases. We provide exceptional healthcare coverage for you and your loved ones, as well as paid leaves and tuition reimbursement for approved programs. Our well-being programs, exciting business travel opportunities, safe working environment, and commitment to social responsibility ensure you thrive personally and professionally. Be part of a team that not only values your contributions but also cares about your growth, well-being, and success. Let's take the leap and experience a fulfilling career with us. Let's go!

title: Senior Data Engineer
summary:
As a Data Engineer, you will be instrumental in helping our customers get insights and value from their data by designing, building, implementing and managing the technical solution and data platform that will enable the delivery and consumption of data. You will have a good understanding of the customer's requirements, needs and business objectives, and be able to translate them into technical data solutions. Not only will you be responsible in ingesting, transforming, cleansing, harmonizing, preparing and structuring data for consumption, you will also help advise on potential ways this can be done better and more efficiently, and leverage on best practices and collective experience to guide our customers to explore options they may not even raise as a requirement but we know will help them in their data and analytics journey.
Job Description:
Designs and develops Data and Analytics solutions
Performs data analysis, data architecture, data engineering activities

title: Data Analytics Manager
summary:
Job description
The objective of the role is to design, develop, deploy, and integrate Advanced Analytics (AA) solutions into different value workstreams and stakeholder journey maps. The Data Analytics Manager will be responsible for: researching and replicating AA best practices; defining AA success measures and gaining sponsorship from Business; and managing technical teams for the development and timely deployment of such use cases into production. He/she will also monitor the effectiveness of deployed AA solutions and recommend ways to continuously improve and scale.
The role reports the Data Analytics Head.
Preferred skills
Strong knowledge and understanding of statistical and Advanced Analytics (AA) methodologies.
Strong knowledge of the phases of model development including model design, feature engineering and transformation, model selection, and performance monitoring
Experienced with data mining and analytics tools, such as AWS Athena and SageMaker
Strong knowledge on the governance of models and AA processes
Good understanding of the ethical principles in analytics and model development
Familiar with model validation processes and documentation, which may include bias and privacy impact assessments
Strong domain knowledge in providing actionable recommendations and insights to different business units, such as Marketing, Customer Experience, Sales, Products, and Operations
Good understanding of marketing attribution, topic modelling, and propensity models
Qualifications
Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's/College Degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Industrial Engineering or any STEM field.
5 to 10 years experienced in the field of Data Science and Analytics
Experience in delivering analytical solutions and performing model maintenance
Experience in querying and pulling data from SQL, SAS, and/or AWS Data Stores
Experience working with projects involving large amount of data to conduct exploratory, descriptive, and predictive analytics
Experience in documenting business metrics and requirements, data lineages and flows, user guides
Ability to communicate effectively and work with stakeholders and end-users at all levels.
Can work independently or as part of team
Must be willing to work with and learn new technologies
Must be action-oriented with excellent follow through
Responsibilities
Collaborating with Business Leads and Journey Owners from Marketing, CX, Sales and Distribution, Operations, Products and Actuarial Teams to identify Advanced Analytics (AA) opportunities, assess impact to journey metrics, and map data requirements
Creating business cases and obtaining sponsor approval for the implementation of AA use cases
Partnering with the Regional Center of Excellence and Global Data Analytics Teams in replicating best practices and contextualizing these to the Philippine market
Designing and implementing analytics solutions and systems, which may include feature selection and engineering, model selection and implementation, documentation, and performance monitoring
Communicating AA requirements and benefits to the different Product and Platform Owners
Co-owning AA models with Business to ensure the successful and timely implementation of AA solutions while in production
Managing the governance of analytics solutions and models, which may include collaborating with the Legal, Risk, Compliance, and Information Security (LRCI) Teams
Translating the results of models and AA solutions into actionable recommendations
Defining AA success metrics and monitoring the effectiveness of recommendations, while consistently identifying ways to iterate, improve, and/or scale AA solutions
Quantifying the potential impact and realized benefits of analytics solutions
Benefits & Others: Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Loans, Vision, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Meal and Transportation Allowance, Business Casual

How You’ll Help Our Team Succeed

 What You’ll Need to Be Successful

title: IT Data Engineer
summary:
Experience your best self with URC!
Universal Robina Corporation is looking for an Enterprise Data Engineer.
The Enterprise Data Engineer is responsible for building data pipelines that are used to transport data from a data source to data lake and/or data warehouse. 
What are the Roles and Responsibilities?
Design, develop and manage data pipelines and orchestrate data integration that meets business requirements.
Identify, design and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-desinging infrastructure for greater scalability.
Work with data and analytics experts to strive for greater functionality in our data systems.
Ensure the data is complete, has been cleansed, and that the rules have been established for outliers (eliminate, ignore, average out and so on).
Identifying patterns, trends and correlations in data sets.
Explore ways to enhance data quality and reliability.
Collaborate with data analys and architect on several projects.
Transforming data sets, quantitative and qualitative analysis into compelling visuals.
What are the Qualifications?
Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's/College Degree in Computer Science/Information Technology, Mathematics or equivalent.
At least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.
Experience with Azure cloud services is a must.
With an in-depth understanding of Data Lake store and Data Warehouse.
Advanced knowledge of SQL and data visualization experience using any BI tool: Microsoft Power BI, Tableau, Qlik. 
COMPANY OVERVIEW
Universal Robina Corporation (URC) is one of the largest branded consumer food and beverage product companies in the Philippines. We’ve built three strong regional brands over the years— Jack 'n Jill for snack foods, C2 Cool and Clean for ready-to-drink tea, and Great Taste for coffee. These brands are becoming popular across the ASEAN region. We also have premium brands from SBA through their snackfoods segment such as Thins, Cheezels, CC’s, Kettle and Natural Chip, Co., and Griffin’s through their high-quality sweet biscuits and wide range of healthy wrapped snacks called Nice and Natural. URC's key to success has been attributed to building strong brands, robust product innovation pipeline, and world-class manufacturing and supply chain capabilities.
OUR PROMISE
We offer multi-industry and International exposure. URC is the major player in various food, agricultural and industrial sectors with a powerful presence throughout the ASEAN Regions.
We advocate a culture of success. URC empowers its people to become holistic individuals and socially responsible leaders.
We are committed to promoting learning and development. URC provides exciting experiences for its people to maximize their potentials and hone their talents. We bring the best in our people and offer them a rewarding career.
OUR CORE PURPOSE
Delight everyone with good food choices.
OUR VALUES
Put people first. We care, cultivate trust, and listen without judgement
Own it. We take initiative to unlock opportunities.
Dare to do. We champion experimentation and incubate new ideas.
Move forward fast. We see the big picture and learn along the way.

title: Data Scientist
summary:
About us 
We are responsible for assessing the success of Dyson’s products in market and identifying the drivers of reliability and satisfaction in our technologies. Using data from a wide range of sources and business domains, we unlock valuable insights that can be fed back into the business to ensure that we continue to delight Dyson owners with innovative and ground-breaking technology.
We push the boundaries of what others have defined as possible. Our approach starts with an engineering mindset and different thinking. Then we continuously refine our ideas – unwilling to compromise and driven by an obsession for finding a better way.
About the role 
We are currently seeking a Data Scientist to join the Business Intelligence (BI) team embedded within the Quality function. We are interested in speaking to people at all Levels (Analyst, Senior and Lead) who have relevant industry experience or skillset.
This role is essential to protect Dyson and its customers from any changes that could impact product reliability or user satisfaction. The role will focus on identifying leading indicators of product quality using data from our manufacturing sites to predict in market performance using established data science techniques. You will need to be comfortable managing and manipulating cloud-based data sources and applying scientific and analytics tools to these datasets. It would be beneficial but not necessary if you have experience of Tableau/Looker/Power BI or a similar visualisation tool that can bring the data to life and ‘tell the story’ to non-technical colleagues of any level.
Creative thinking & persistence is a prerequisite of this role and necessary attributes for explaining the key drivers of any trends and features identified.
As well as BI colleagues you will collaborate closely with product and category engineers, IT and data infrastructure teams as-well-as external and internal manufacturing and operational teams across the globe.
About you 
Practical application of data science tools, techniques and methodologies.
Relevant experience in Cloud Data Analysis e.g., BigQuery (or Redshift or Snowflake).
Proficient in leveraging Python for comprehensive data analysis (optional: machine learning).
Demonstrated expertise in applying advanced statistical techniques such as hypothesis testing.
Basic knowledge of data engineering tools such as DBT and ETL techniques.
Adept at articulating findings effectively, both visually and verbally, and constructing compelling narratives to management.
Desirable to have experience in the logistics, supply chain or manufacturing domain, such as MES (Manufacturing Execution Systems).
Desirable to have experience with Tableau, Looker, Qlik or Power BI for data visualization.
Relevant experience in project and stakeholder management.
Forward thinking and thrives on change with the ability to deliver under pressure.
Interested in how business works and desire to improve our performance.
Self-motivated, dynamic and results driven.
Team player, comfortable dealing with all business levels.
Ethical, personal integrity.
Attention to detail without losing bigger picture.
Dyson is an equal opportunity employer. We know that great minds don’t think alike, and it takes all kinds of minds to make our technology so unique. We welcome applications from all backgrounds and employment decisions are made without regard to race, colour, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other any other dimension of diversity.

title: ETL Developer
summary:
Job Details:
Create, modify, and delete objects/tables in S3 buckets, including the raw, clean, curated zones, and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster).
  Develop and execute Glue Jobs scripts for Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, ensuring efficient data transformation across the entire dataset in the Data Lake.
  Determine appropriate actions, such as tokenization, to be applied in the raw zone for immediate data processing.
  Set up dataset alarms to monitor the data pipeline and define notifications for missing data ingested.
  Collaborate with stakeholders to determine data transformation requirements for selected datasets within the Data Lake.
  Apply data standardization techniques in the clean zone to ensure consistent and reliable data quality.
  Create snapshots in the clean zone to capture data at specific points in time for analysis and auditing purposes.
  Design and develop data models in the curated zone, optimizing data structures for efficient access and retrieval.
  Define tables/objects in the curated zone to support Salesforce usage, ensuring data integrity and compatibility.
  Identify and create tables/objects in the curated zone and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster) for Tableau standard access.
  Determine tables/objects to be included in Redshift Spectrum for Tableau advanced access, enabling advanced data exploration and analysis.
Skills:
AWS Console, including S3, Glue, and Redshift services, ETL processes, scripting, and data transformation techniques, Glue Data Catalog and its usage in ETL workflows, understanding of data lakes, data modeling, and database concepts.
Ability to collaborate effectively with cross functional teams and stakeholders. • Strong problem solving and analytical skills. • Excellent communication and documentation skills. • Attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high quality results. • Willing to travel and be deployed to client/affiliate off shore (Hong Kong office)

Bachelor's/College Degree
Minimum of 3 years’ relevant work experience
Good Communication Skills

title: Engineer - Greenhouse Gas (GHG) Accounting
summary:
Summary of role:
Our Climate Practice offers a comprehensive suite of services to help companies measure and manage the risks and opportunities they face from climate change. These services include the development of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions inventories and action plans to reduce emissions, and the procurement of carbon offsets and renewable energy. The Climate Practice comprises over 200 practitioners led by industry-recognized experts. We have a track record in successfully addressing cutting-edge issues and we have deep connections and partnerships with NGOs and other standard-setting organizations that help shape the corporate sustainability field. And we deploy start-of-the-art software for data collection, emissions inventory development and data visualization.
We are looking for an experienced practitioner in GHG accounting to join the Climate Practice. You will lead the development of GHG emissions inventories, work with team members in North America and Europe to provide clients with actionable insights that inform their sustainability strategy, and provide technical direction to team members in the Philippines and oversight of their work. Your projects and clients will span across a diverse set of industries, ranging from Fortune 500 companies to boutique brands, and require engagement with clients, and their suppliers, around the world.
Key Responsibilities:
Support the delivery of GHG inventorying services, including operational scope 1+2 and value chain scope 3 inventories, FLAG GHG accounting, and voluntary and regulated compliance advisory services
Provide guidance and technical leadership to clients as well as colleagues on leading practices, standards, and trends, incorporating this knowledge into consulting projects
Support the development of decarbonization action plans for clients, including science-based targets (SBT) and net zero targets
Communicate complex technical ideas to non-technical stakeholders
Participate in the development of the Anthesis’ innovative processes and tools to collect, analyze, and visualize sustainability metrics, especially GHG emissions
Skills:
Bachelor’s degree in engineering, environmental science, mathematics, statistics, economics or related field or equivalent practical experience
At least 2-3 years of relevant experience in corporate environmental sustainability, acquired either in-house or in a consultancy environment, with a focus on corporate GHG accounting (scopes 1, 2 and 3)
Proficiency in calculating and reporting scope 1, 2 and 3 emissions, with experience in key topic areas, including setting inventory boundaries, and accounting for renewable energy and supply chain emissions
Demonstrated experience in developing GHG inventories with organizations across multiple sectors (retail, manufacturing, financial, energy, etc.)
Familiarity with carbon accounting and reporting standards and programs (e.g., ISO 14064, GHG Protocol, TCR)
Experience with third-party audits of inventories, and with auditors/assurance providers
Experience in broader ESG strategy, data analytics, and/or preparation of corporate disclosures (CDP, GRI, SASB)
Skilled in synthesizing and analyzing quantitative data
Skilled in using Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Word, PowerPoint). Intermediate Excel knowledge required.
Desirable skills:
Experience supporting supplier engagement programs focused on climate change and supplier-level emissions reductions
Experience with data visualization using PowerBI or Tableau
Project management experience
Personal Attributes and Qualities:
Strong written and verbal communication skills in English
Curious, globally minded, and enthusiastic.
Organized, methodical, and analytical.
Effective time management and organizational skills. Ability to respond positively to pressure and take a flexible approach to a dynamic, fast moving and changing work environment.

title: ETL Developer | Work from Home | GA
summary:
We are seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our team. As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for managing and optimizing data workflows within the AWS Console. Your primary focus will be on creating, modifying, and deleting objects/tables in S3 buckets, executing Glue Jobs scripts for ETL processes, and utilizing the Glue Data Catalog for ETL operations.
Responsibilities:
Create, modify, and delete objects/tables in S3 buckets, including the raw, clean, curated zones, and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster).
Develop and execute Glue Jobs scripts for Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, ensuring efficient data transformation across the entire dataset in the Data Lake.
Determine appropriate actions, such as tokenization, to be applied in the raw zone for immediate data processing.
Set up dataset alarms to monitor the data pipeline and define notifications for missing data ingested.
Collaborate with stakeholders to determine data transformation requirements for selected datasets within the Data Lake.
Apply data standardization techniques in the clean zone to ensure consistent and reliable data quality.
Create snapshots in the clean zone to capture data at specific points in time for analysis and auditing purposes.
Design and develop data models in the curated zone, optimizing data structures for efficient access and retrieval.
Define tables/objects in the curated zone to support Salesforce usage, ensuring data integrity and compatibility.
Identify and create tables/objects in the curated zone and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster) for Tableau standard access.
Determine tables/objects to be included in Redshift Spectrum for Tableau advanced access, enabling advanced data exploration and analysis.
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information technology, or a related field.
Minimum of 3 years’ relevant work experience.
Strong proficiency in working with the AWS Console, including S3, Glue, and Redshift services.
Experience with ETL processes, scripting, and data transformation techniques.
Familiarity with Glue Data Catalog and its usage in ETL workflows.
Solid understanding of data lakes, data modeling, and database concepts.
Ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and stakeholders.
Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.
Excellent communication and documentation skills.
Attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high-quality results.

title: Data Engineer (Python and ETL) | WFH
summary:
SUMMARY OF RESPONSIBILITIES 
The primary responsibility of the Data Engineer is to prepare and transform data using pipelines. This involves extracting data from various data sources or systems, transforming it into the staging area, and loading these into the Global Compliance data repositories, including SharePoint and SQL Server. He/she shall ensure that the transformation of raw,unstructured data into defined formats will be useful for the BI Developers, Reports Analysts, and Auditors.
The Data Engineer is also responsible for expanding and optimizing the Global Compliance data and data pipeline architectures, as well as optimizing data flow and data collection for cross-functional teams. The ideal candidate is an experienced data pipeline builder and data wrangler who enjoys optimizing data systems and building them from the ground up with limited supervision.
The Data Engineer is also responsible for finding trends in data sets and developing algorithms to help make raw data more useful to the Global Compliance team. He/she must possess a set of technical skills, including a deep knowledge of SQL database design and preferably, object-oriented/object function scripting languages such as Python.
The Data Engineer must possess relevant experience in project management and organizational skills; advanced working SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases.
EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE
·        Graduate degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Information System, Applied Mathematics, or recipient of any
·        certifications related to Data Engineering
·        With more than 2 years of experience in using Python
·         With more than 2 years of experience in data engineering, data mining processes, date pipelining, and building of data warehouse
·        Experience in SQL Management and Administration, preferably Microsoft MS SQL 2017 or latest version
·         Experience in Windows Server Administration
·        Experience in manipulating, structuring and monitoring big datasets
·         Experience in implementing ETL/ELT procedures, data mining processes, date pipelining, and building of data warehouse
·         Experience with Restful API
·         Experience with Azure PAAS (Platform-As-A-Service)
·         Experience with Power Automate and Power Shell
·         Experience with SFTP/Shell Scripting
·        Knowledgeable in MSStack Platform
·        Strong Knowledge with Pandas, Selenium, OS, Pyodbc, Regex, Xlsxwingst, Numpy, SQL Alchemy, Apache
·        Experience with Azure Data Factory (ADF).
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Loans, Business (e.g. Shirts), Shifting Schedules

Come and join us! 
  Why NetSuite
One word — transformation.
Come and join us! At NetSuite, we believe the cloud is here to stay and so do our 20,000+ customers. NetSuite is simply redefining business around the globe by providing a cloud-based, unified system that delivers outstanding capabilities to drive business forward. Founded in 1998 as THE cloud ERP pioneer, today NetSuite has transformed the business operations of our customers without the high costs and inefficiency of on-premise systems.
Transform your career at NetSuite
At NetSuite, we work hard, and we work thoughtfully. We hire steadfast competitors. We hire individuals that are daring trail blazers. NetSuite employees take the hill, we prefer action over inaction, we are diligent in our mission, and we pause only to celebrate our success. And we DO celebrate, because if you don’t have fun along the way, then what’s the point? NetSuite is redefining how its customers do business.
Summary:
The Shared Services Group within Oracle NetSuite Professional Services is chartered to assist and guide our customers by developing analytic reporting strategies and solutions, creating implementation roadmaps, performing assessments, and full-life cycle implementations of analytics solutions.
We are looking for an experienced consultant/developer with significant hands-on experience working with NetSuite SuiteAnalytics Connect, integration, ETL and data warehouse solutions to assist Oracle NetSuite’s clients with their data warehouse implementation. Knowledge of related solutions such as Oracle Analytics Cloud (OAC) and NetSuite SuiteAnalytics Connect, and Autonomous Data Warehouse (ADW) and Oracle Fusion Analytics Warehouse (FAW) desired.
Key Responsibilities:
Consultatively gathering customer requirements and collaborate with the customer to define the business challenge the customer is attempting to better understand with data
Taking the defined business objective, using the understanding of the data model and producing analytics to deliver actionable insights
Identify new data and product patterns through data mining and communicate those complex concepts and the results of the analyses in a clear and effective manner through creative visualization directly to company executives
Extend the data warehouse by incorporating data from 3rd party datasets/applications
Build data pipelines from multiple data sources by performing necessary ETL tasks including processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis
Lead project delivery as a technical expert when implementing solutions.
Develop solutions that follow product development guidelines and are in-line with established design standards and approved architectures.
Transfer product knowledge to customers to reinforce training and ensure adoption.
Resolve or advance client issues as appropriate to support and engineering teams.
Develop and maintain up-to-date knowledge of Oracle and NetSuite analytics, data integration products and service offerings.
Work closely with the NetSuite Product Team to influence design, product features and roadmap.
Attend internal meetings and collaborate by sharing knowledge and standard methodologies within the practice including mentoring sessions for junior resources, and other central initiatives.
Support pre-sales efforts and drive technology adoption by positioning Oracle NetSuite Consulting services.
Preferred Qualifications/Skills include:
At least 8 to 10 years of experience in OBIEE/Hyperion/Oracle Analytics Cloud, Data Warehouse, and SQL experience ideally with integration to/from Oracle NetSuite Application
Solid understanding of Oracle Database, Data Modelling, Oracle SQL Developer, Data Warehouse concepts, advanced analytics concepts, and implementation.
Experience implementing and using Big Data and visualization techniques, tools, and technologies (Spark, Kafka, Tableau, etc.)

title: Data Analytics/Data Scientist (es)
summary:
DATA ANALYST
As a Data Analyst, you will be tasked with managing all aspects of any new work/project assessments thoroughly from inception to delivery. You will need to build close working relationships with chief data office to design and implement specific data requirements based on bank’s data standards. In addition, as Data Analyst you will also work closely with Project teams, partners, and 3rd party vendors.
This role is very exciting as it provides the candidate opportunity to work with Business and IT partners, learn Banks Businesses/Products/Processes and to develop relationship with senior stakeholders.

·        Act as SME for all Data sourcing, Data modelling, data quality requirements

·        Support transition of data quality and data governance capabilities into BAU

Data Visualization – This role highly requires data story telling skills using data visualization tools like MicroStrategy, Tableau etc.

·        Good planning and forward-thinking skills.
·        Ability to work independently and able to assist team members in their strategies.
·        Excellent verbal and written communication skills
·        Good organizational and documentation skills are essential
DATA ANALYTICS
This role as Senior Data Analyst run data projects in Agile / SCRUM manner. Role is very exciting as it provides the candidate opportunity to work with Business and IT partners, learn Banks Businesses/Products/Processes and to develop relationship with stakeholders.
Key Roles and Responsibilities 
Translate business requirements to user stories
Work closely with Product owner/Scrum master to ensure the Backlog is up-to-date and User stories are ready for sprint planning.
Act as SME for all data sourcing, data modelling, data quality requirements for the applications.
Understand the business process, workflow required to guide Agile team so that data requirements are covered completely and correctly.
Actively participate and contribute in SCRUM planning, SCRUM stand-up and Sprint retrospective meetings.
Provide leadership guidance and support to team.
Help and Support SCRUM team on UAT and sign-off from Ops teams.
Engage with data architect and keep them updated on project progress and take their inputs while designing the data requirements for the applications assigned.
Provide inputs to PSC and other Project meetings.
Identify and raise risks well in advance so that they can be managed.
Other duties as assigned 
Qualifications and Skills 
Minimum of 7 years of Banking industry work experience with a focus on change management. Preferred: Experience as a BA/Data Analyst in projects. Experience with data analytics and visualization tools
Minimum of 7 years of experience in large-scale projects/programs with multiple dependencies within and across organizational boundaries. Preferred: Experience in Agile / Scrum approach.

• Define tables/objects in the curated zone to support Salesforce usage, ensuring data integrity and compatibility.

title: ETL Developer (WFH/Remote)
summary:
What’s the scoop?
We're seeking a scripting and automation wizard who thrives on innovative problem-solving, crafts efficient solutions, and constantly enhances our data infrastructure. Join our dynamic startup, reporting to the Director of Product, collaborating closely with the ETL team, and becoming the data connections guru. Embrace remote work with our strong team culture, featuring daily meetings, quarterly reviews, and an annual in-person retreat.
Join the ride and find out why we're the 2023 Philippines' Fastest Growing Offshore Staffing Company and Great Place to Work Certified!
What you’ll do
In this role, you will be responsible for the maintenance of existing ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes, the creation of new ETL jobs from existing data sources, and the development of entirely new data connectors. Your tasks will involve retrieving compressed files in .zip format from FTP servers, extracting their contents, merging multiple files into a unified .csv format, and subsequently uploading this data to our central data warehouse.
Additionally, you will be tasked with making HTTP POST requests to APIs, retrieving JSON data, and transforming it into .csv files before transferring these files to our data warehouse. Another aspect of your role will involve interacting with web-based interfaces through browser automation. This will entail requesting data exports, monitoring the export process, initiating downloads, and performing file renaming procedures prior to uploading the data to our data warehouse.
It's important to note that our ETL pipelines are designed to be fully automated, and we prioritize minimizing manual interventions and avoiding solutions that generate technical debt. These principles are integral to our approach.
What to bring
 3+ years of experience in Python writing automated ETLs
Experience using Selenium browser automation (or a similar tool)
Ability to move data from one system to another via REST API, FTP, and native SDKs
Strong understanding of data files and the ability to transform them (JSON, .csv, .xlsx, .txt)
Working knowledge of SQL and the ability to write basic queries
Diligent with commenting, documentation, and version control
Bachelor’s degree required
Must be able to provide examples of work products (example projects)
Willing to work on a night shift.
Benefits & Others: Dental, Medical, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Casual (e.g. T-shirts), Hybrid, Work From Home, or Flexible work arrangement.

title: Python Flask Software Developer
company: The British Council Philippine Branch Office
summary:
About the Programme
The Government of the Republic of the Philippines with the support of the European Union is implementing the Justice Sector Reform Programme: Governance in Justice II (GOJUST II). GOJUST II builds on and continues the work of the predecessor programme, GOJUST that was implemented from April 2016 to September 2020. GOJUST II is implemented in joint co-financing with the Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation. The overall objective of GOJUST is to contribute to inclusive and sustainable socio-economic development through improved access to justice for all in the Philippines. Specifically, it aims to develop more responsive and accountable justice services. It includes two components focusing on justice and human rights, respectively. The programme is being implemented from December 2020 to June 2025.
GOJUST II seeks to achieve four major result areas, as follows:
Result 1: Justice sector coordination mechanisms are improved
Result 2: Strengthened institutional efficiency and effectiveness in the delivery of justice services
Result 3: Increased access to the justice system for vulnerable groups, including women
Result 4: Justice policy and practice is informed by evidence and responds to justice needs
About the Role
Global Objective
To facilitate timely data exchange among criminal justice agencies through the digital and automated data sharing through the development and implementation of the National Justice Information System (NJIS). The objective of this mission contributes to Result 1 on justice sector coordination and Result 2 focusing on strengthening institutional efficiency and effectiveness in the delivery of justice services.
Specific Objectives
To support the development of the NJIS middleware exchange platform and to the inter-operability layer of the NJIS implementing agencies
To facilitate data harmonisation, particularly in the nomenclature of criminal offenses through the development of Application Program Interface of the Philippine Crime Index Research System
To contribute to jail decongestion by enhancing/refactoring the Bureau of Corrections Inmate Management Information Systems including the updating of the Good Conduct Time allowance computation
To ensure whenever possible, gender disaggregation of data in existing databases in terms of sex, age, ethnicity, disability, among other categories to contribute to gender-responsive and inclusive data analysis
Qualifications and Experience Required
Skills and Competencies
Fluent in spoken and written English
Excellent analytical competence and technical skills, and detail oriented
Excellent interpersonal skills
Active listening skills and strong writing skills
Ability to coordinate and communicate with key stakeholders
Qualifications and skills
A college graduate with a degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or any related course
Knowledge of the Software development life-cycle
General Professional Experience
At least one (1) year of relevant work experience in Software Development that includes writing, modifying, and testing codes and scripts to allow computer software and applications to function properly
Experience working on a variety of software development projects
Specific Professional Experience
Highly proficient in Python and JavaScript language programming
At least one (1) year of experience working in Python and JavaScript Coding Environments
Scope of Work and Outputs
The scope of work shall include the support for the following activities, among others:
Kick-off meeting with the Technical Assistance Team (TAT) and with the Department of Justice
Participate in a training on Gender Equity and Social Inclusion (GESI)
With supervision/instructions from the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer, develop the following with the team composed of systems developers:
NJIS Middleware Exchange Platform
Interoperability layers of the NJIS implementing agencies
Enhancements/ refactoring of the Bureau of Corrections Inmate Management Information Systems that includes the updating of the Good Conduct Time allowance computation
Development of API of the Philippine Crime Index Research System (PCIRS)
Presentation of the output and findings to the Technical Assistance Team (TAT) and to the relevant officials of the DOJ and the NJIS implementing agencies, including recommendations for further redevelopment of the different applications, including entry points for disaggregation of cases, which could support gender-responsive and inclusive analysis.
The output of this engagement is the following:
Submit an inception report to the Technical Assistance Team no later than two (2) weeks after the commencement of the agreement containing the following:
over-all approach and methodology, including entry points for disaggregation of data and categorisation of cases
detailed workplan for the delivery services
workflow design that includes a process of quality assurance
Software Requirement Specifications (SRS) for the applications to be developed
Implementation Plan
Prototype of the applications
Training materials, training module, and training report
Monthly status report on the project's progress signed by the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer or representation on the following:
project status report including percentage completion of the project

title: Data Scientist
summary:
JOB OBJECTIVES
This position is accountable for executing duties pertaining to data management, analytics, data engineering and data science set forth by management and industry standards and to be able to deliver data requirements by different stake holders. 
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
Serve as a subject matter expert on providing technical specialization catering data analytics and data engineering, who advocates for actional data-driven decision making, and demonstrates an “Intelligent Analytics” mentality within and across functions.
Drive and lead initiatives to enable managers and other department heads to interpret and appreciate results, through education, easy to understand tools, intelligent reports, or dashboards.
Holds pragmatic understanding of different strategic and operational models applied in organizations.
Experience in Supply Chain Management or Manufacturing industry is a big plus. It is strongly recommended that the applicant will at least have the theoretical understanding of Supply Chain Management
Hold ability to ask critical question during brainstorming session with stakeholders and colleagues.
Formulate the scope and analyze business problems by creating chain of analysis and using justifiable metrics through different complex datasets.
Has ability to understand complex datasets and distill the complexity into simpler actionable insights through BI tools and dashboards using tools such as PowerBI(preferred) or Tableau
Create, optimize, and apply algorithms in applications supporting different business decisions in the company.
Practical understanding of updated machine learning techniques and the foundational mathematics with an acumen to apply them to solve complex business challenges.
Holds ability to explain complex pipelines pertaining to Data Processing, Data Extraction, Feature Engineering, Modelling etc. in simpler terms to stakeholders.
Has excellent presentation, communication, and Data storytelling skills.
Has ability to transfer knowledge to their immediate juniors and colleagues within and across different departments.
MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS
A. Education
Bachelor’s/college degree in Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication), Computer Science/Management Information Systems or College degree, preferably in Computer Science or equivalent experience or in Statistics. Masters’ Degree in Data Science, Computer science, applied mathematics, statistics, machine learning, Economics or Physics. PhD is a big plus
B. Expertise
Candidate has:
At least 5 years of experience in creating data pipelines using SQL and Python
At least 5 years of experience in creating production ready Enterprise and Functional Dashboards using tools like PowerBI or Tableau
Has more than 5 years of experience in creating data end to end data and ETL pipelines using the cloud resources such as Azure or AWS. Azure is preferred.
Has a strong background in creating Descriptive and Inferential Statistical Analysis for all the analytics related projects
Has at least 5 years of experience in data management and ability to perform complex queries using SQL. Ability to query big data using Spark or spark is a big plus
Has a strong command in doing Data wrangling, Data Cleaning and Data Governance of structured and unstructured data
Understanding and knowledge of emerging technologies pertaining to AI, ML, IOT, robotics, etc.  
Has at least 3 years of experience in creating technical solutions with additional 2 or more years in managing or leading a team in the field of analytics or data science
Holds experience in implementing Data engineering using cloud resource in Enterprise data lakes or data warehouses. Familiarity with ETL using Azure cloud resources is a big added advantage
Has a strong command in using scripting languages such as Python or R. Python is recommended.
Familiarity with MLOps techniques for managing and deploying models at scale on Cloud (Azure preferred). It’s not recommended but will hold a significant advantage 
C. Skills/Competencies
Solid foundation of technical and analytical skills with proficiency in OLTP and OLAP systems
Aptitude, interest, analytical and problem-solving skills to perform data manipulations.
Good written and oral communication and interpersonal skills to be able to effectively deal with subordinates, peers, superiors as well as external vendors and service providers.
Benefits & Others: Medical, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Business (e.g. Shirts)

Job description
We are seeking highly skilled and motivated professionals to join our dynamic team as Database Developers, Data Engineers, and Data Analysts. As part of our organization's data-driven initiatives, you will play a critical role in designing, developing, and maintaining our database systems, implementing efficient data pipelines, and extracting valuable insights from our data assets.
Responsibilities will include, but are not limited to
1. Database Development:
- Design and develop robust and scalable database solutions to meet the organization's data requirements.
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand data needs and optimize database structures for performance and efficiency.
- Implement data integrity and security measures to ensure the confidentiality and accuracy of data.
- Write and optimize SQL queries, stored procedures, and triggers for seamless data access and manipulation.
2. Data Engineering:
- Build and maintain data pipelines to ingest, process, and transform data from various sources into our centralized data repository.
- Integrate data from disparate systems and sources, ensuring data consistency and reliability.
- Monitor data pipeline performance and troubleshoot any issues to ensure smooth data flow.
- Implement data quality checks and data validation processes to maintain data accuracy and consistency.
3. Data Analysis:
- Utilize data analysis tools and techniques to explore and interpret large datasets to identify patterns, trends, and insights.
- Collaborate with stakeholders to understand their analytical needs and provide data-driven recommendations to support decision-making.
- Develop and maintain interactive dashboards and reports to communicate data-driven insights effectively.
- Perform ad-hoc data analysis to address specific business questions and challenges.
Qualifications:
- Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Science, or related fields.
- Proven experience in database development, data engineering, and/or data analysis roles.
- Strong proficiency in SQL and hands-on experience with database management systems (e.g., MS SQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle).
- Familiarity with ETL processes and data integration techniques.
- Proficiency in one or more programming languages (e.g., Python, Java, Scala) for data processing and manipulation.
- Experience with data modeling, data warehousing concepts, and data architecture best practices.
- Knowledge of data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) and statistical analysis tools (e.g., R, Python) is a plus.
- Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work with large, complex datasets.
- Excellent communication skills to collaborate effectively with team members and stakeholders.
- Proactive attitude towards problem-solving and the ability to take initiative in addressing data-related challenges.
- Positive interpersonal skills to foster a collaborative and supportive work environment.
- Adaptability and flexibility to work in a fast-paced and evolving data environment.

title: Senior Data Analyst (SQL/Kettle)
summary:
Job Description Summary
Responsible for performing in-depth data analysis and developing complex ad-hoc reports to meet business needs. Deploy, troubleshoot, and resolve data issues, conducting data research, and ensure data quality.
BASIC FUNCTIONS: This position performs data management and analysis tasks within a specific functional area or data type. Requires heavy communication with data sources/contacts.
Responsibilities:
• Identify, research, and analyze data so that it can be accurately processed
• Perform data analysis for assigned business including design and develop of critical ad hoc reports.
• Perform structured quality assurance testing including the development of a test plan and scripts.
• Proactively identify issues in data that need to be fixed.
• Perform detailed data verification and validation, proactively identify data issues. Responsible for data issues escalation and resolution.
• Make process and/or system improvement recommendations to assist the business in achieving its goals and objectives.
• Works across business/teams to collect, aggregate, match, consolidate, and confirm data for quality and accuracy
• Gather reporting requirements for change requests and ad-hoc reports as requested
• Utilize expertise and mentor others in use of data analysis tools, techniques, reporting and analytical applications.
• May assist with acquisition, extracting, transforming and standing up of various data sets
• May design and/or develop and ensure the quality of specific databases for collection, tracking, and reporting of research data.
• Perform other duties as assigned.
Qualifications:
• Bachelor’s Degree in any course
• 3+ years’ experience reporting, analysis or related field
• Expertise with MS Office (MS Access, MS Word, MS Excel).
• Demonstrated experience with data manipulation and analysis
• Working knowledge of relational databases a plus
• Strong ad-hoc SQL, ETL, Kettle or Java query development, SAS or C++ skills
• Experience working with data analytics-driven solutions with sensitive data sources
• High degree of creative, analytical and problem solving skills;
• The ability to gather and interpret information and to develop, recommend and implement solutions;
• Team oriented – ability to build departmental and cross-functional relationships.
TECHNICAL SKILLS:
• Proficiency with development languages such as SQL, UNIX, Linux, XML, HPCC, etc.
• Proficiency with various data types and formats including, but not limited to: XML, flat files, delimited, etc.
• Proficiency with KETTLE- ETL application
• Proficiency with data analysis tools and processes.
• Excellent proofreading skills to see how data and facts can be linked together to create more meaningful conclusions.
• Ability and desire to learn new processes, tools, and technologies.
• Strong research skills.
• Attention to detail.
• Strong oral and written communications skills.
ACCOUNTABILITIES:
• Business support through data analysis and research.
• Modify pre-designed queries to assess data for research purposes.
• Independently run data statistics, including coverage stats, field populations, etc.
• Run data profiles.
• Support business or other data engineering teams with data subject matter expertise.
• Complete new data evaluations to diverse audiences.
• Create data documentation including mappings and quality thresholds.
• Investigate, track, and report data issues.
• Conducts data review and verification and ensures corrections/clarifications are made in a timely manner.
• Strong level of intimacy within a specific data content area.
• Provide technical problem solving to less technical teams (customer service, consumer advocacy, etc.).
• Undertake and complete new data onboarding and/or production data management functions as assigned/required.
• Utilize various data workflow management and analysis tools.
• Resolve and/or guide data sources in resolving basic data issues within specific functional area or data type.
• Produce basic ad hoc data counts, stats, examples as required.
• All other duties as assigned.
Why join us?
Competitive salary with annual increase and incentive.
Career Development Programs
24 Paid Time-offs annually, 30 Paid Time-offs on the 5th year
Comprehensive HMO for you and up to 4 Dependents
Day 1 Life and Accident Insurance
Flexible Retirement Plan
Hybrid Work Set up. 
IT equipment will be provided.
For your convenience, our entire recruitment process is done virtually.
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Parking, Monthly Performance Bonus, Free HMO benefit on Day 1, Retirement package, Business Attire, Mondays-Fridays but may also vary depending on role

title: Data Engineer (Azure Data Warehousing)
summary:
Emerson’s 132 years of history have been filled with achievements and challenges that have driven innovative thinking and bold transformations, molding us into the company we are today. By joining us as a Data Engineer, you will support Business Intelligence using the Azure suite of Analytics and Data platforms.
In this capacity, you will be focusing on the technical aspects and implementation of data gathering, integration, and model design, along with some report and dashboard creation. You will use Azure DevOps, Azure Synapse Analytics, and Power BI to create data models for strategic and self-service business intelligence. This gives you a very vital role in helping drive growth platforms and supporting operational pillars while striving for long-term value creation.
If this sounds like a perfect fit for you, apply now and join our team in Quezon City, Philippines! All roles are currently on a blended Work-From-Home arrangement, and company-provided IT assets are given on your first day. Enjoy our market-competitive pay, comprehensive benefits package, well-being programs, and career development opportunities.
In This Role, Your Responsibilities Will Be:
To implement robust data pipelines in Azure.
To build reusable and scalable data pipelines.
To develop and deploy new data platforms, data warehouses, data marts, etc.
To use Azure BI services to support strategic and self-service models and reports.
To work closely with the product owners and architects to develop Azure Data Platforms.
To practice internal standards for coding, project tracking, and documentation.
To integrate data from source systems/data lake into a data warehouse.
Who You Are:
You have a strong drive for results and exhibit passion and enthusiasm to get things done. You are a proactive self-starter with a high level of commitment to exceeding expectations. You can efficiently carry out tasks independently and generate accurate, high-quality reports. You can proficiently communicate ideas and influence both internal and external customers. You're interpersonally savvy and able to collaborate and efficiently work with people at any level in a multicultural environment.

title: Lead Python Flask Software Developer
company: The British Council Philippine Branch Office
summary:
About the Programme
The Government of the Republic of the Philippines with the support of the European Union is implementing the Justice Sector Reform Programme: Governance in Justice II (GOJUST II). GOJUST II builds on and continues the work of the predecessor programme, GOJUST that was implemented from April 2016 to September 2020. GOJUST II is implemented in joint co-financing with the Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation. The overall objective of GOJUST is to contribute to inclusive and sustainable socio-economic development through improved access to justice for all in the Philippines. Specifically, it aims to develop more responsive and accountable justice services. It includes two components focusing on justice and human rights, respectively. The programme is being implemented from December 2020 to June 2025.
GOJUST II seeks to achieve four major result areas, as follows:
Result 1: Justice sector coordination mechanisms are improved
Result 2: Strengthened institutional efficiency and effectiveness in the delivery of justice services
Result 3: Increased access to the justice system for vulnerable groups, including women
Result 4: Justice policy and practice is informed by evidence and responds to justice needs
About the Role
Global Objective
To facilitate timely data exchange among criminal justice agencies through the digital and automated data sharing through the development and implementation of the National Justice Information System (NJIS). The objective of this mission contributes to Result 1 on justice sector coordination and Result 2 focusing on strengthening institutional efficiency and effectiveness in the delivery of justice services.
Specific Objectives
To support the development of the NJIS middleware exchange platform and to the inter-operability layer of the NJIS implementing agencies
To facilitate data harmonisation, particularly in the nomenclature of criminal offenses through the development of Application Program Interface of the Philippine Crime Index Research System
To contribute to jail decongestion by enhancing/refactoring the Bureau of Corrections Inmate Management Information Systems including the updating of the Good Conduct Time allowance computation
To ensure whenever possible, gender disaggregation of data in existing databases in terms of sex, age, ethnicity, disability, among other categories to contribute to gender-responsive and inclusive data analysis
Qualifications and Experience Required
Skills and Competencies
Fluent in spoken and written English
Excellent analytical competence and technical skills, and detail oriented
Excellent interpersonal skills
Active listening skills and strong writing skills
Ability to coordinate and communicate with key stakeholders
Qualifications and skills
A college graduate with a degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or any related course
Fluent in English and Filipino.
Ability to prioritise critical tasks and work well in an output-driven environment
Coaching and mentoring skills
Organisational abilities
Administrative skills
Good communication skills, both written and verbal
The ability to work independently and as a part of the team
Accuracy and good attention to detail
The ability to work under pressure and tight deadlines
A positive approach in a busy working environment
A good understanding of data confidentiality
General Professional Experience
At least five (5) years of relevant work experience as a Lead Systems Developer which includes experience in:
Ensuring that codes meet the technical specifications and are delivered on time
Directing other Systems developers in the design, development, testing, and debugging
Designing, building, and configuring applications to meet business process and application requirements
Writing testable, scalable, and efficient code and leading code reviews
Specific Professional Experience
At least five (5) years’ experience in web development preferably with experience in Python: Flask framework
Knowledgeable with front-end Javascript libraries/frameworks such as ReactJS
Familiarity with Linux operating systems and experience in developing on the Linux platform
Strong knowledge in database technologies, SQL, ORM, and other relevant technologies
Experience in Git workflow is an advantage
Scope of Work and Outputs
The scope of work shall include the support for the following activities, among others:
Kick-off meeting with the Technical Assistance Team (TAT) and with the Department of Justice
Participate in a training on Gender Equity and Social Inclusion (GESI)
With supervision/instructions from the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer, develop the following with the team composed of system analyst and systems developers:
NJIS Middleware Exchange Platform
Interoperability layers of the NJIS implementing agencies
Enhancements/ refactoring of the Bureau of Corrections Inmate Management Information Systems that includes the updating of the Good Conduct Time allowance computation
Development of API of the Philippine Crime Index Research System (PCIRS)
Presentation of the output and findings to the Technical Assistance Team (TAT) and to the relevant officials of the DOJ and the NJIS implementing agencies, including recommendations for further redevelopment of the different applications, including entry points for disaggregation of cases, which could support gender-responsive and inclusive analysis.
The output of this engagement is the following:
Submit an inception report to the Technical Assistance Team no later than two (2) weeks after the commencement of the agreement containing the following:
over-all approach and methodology, including entry points for disaggregation of data and categorisation of cases
detailed workplan for the delivery services
workflow design that includes a process of quality assurance
Software Requirement Specifications (SRS) for the applications to be developed
Implementation Plan
Prototype of the applications
Training materials, training module, and training report
Monthly status report on the project's progress signed by the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer or representation on the following:
project status report including percentage completion of the project
project status report shall include information on the compliance with the quality assurance process indicated in the workplan
Submit a Mission Report upon completion of the engagement, structured as follows:
Executive summary
Introduction and Background
Main findings related to the overall and specific objectives of the assignment
Key Recommendations, including entry points for gender-related disaggregation of data
Conclusion
Relevant Annexes including the SRS, Implementation Plan, training modules, training materials, and training report
All software codes, documentations, training modules, and related project artifacts shall also be included in the submission of the final mission report
Reporting and communication
The Lead Systems Developer shall report directly to the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer (DOJ-CITO). Together with a team of systems developers, they will supplement the DOJ technical staff to develop various components of the NJIS. The DOJ CITO shall have complete control and supervision of the work assigned to the project.
The Lead Systems Developer involved in the project shall sign a confidentiality and non-disclosure agreement with the DOJ.
The Lead Systems Developer will be required to provide the Services in the Philippines and such other locations as may be agreed between the parties in writing from time to time.
All documentation and source code pertaining to this project shall be endorsed to the Department of Justice – Chief Information Technology Officer after completion.
All reports and correspondence must be in English.
All reports must be submitted electronically in the format provided at the start of the mission. Comments by the Technical Assistance Team and key stakeholders on the various reports, will be provided as soon as possible. Draft final reports must be submitted to the Technical Assistance Team. 
Duration
18 months
Application Requirements:
Submit a Pricing Approach indicating the monthly rate in PHP. Kindly factor in all possible costs in the delivery of the outputs. Official business travels will be shouldered by the British Council (GOJUST II Programme) based on British Council standard rates.
Send your cover letter and CV by 20 September 2023; 11:59 PM Manila time.

title: ETL Developer
summary:
We are seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our team. As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for managing and optimizing data workflows within the AWS Console. Your primary focus will be on creating, modifying, and deleting objects/tables in S3 buckets, executing Glue Jobs scripts for ETL processes, and utilizing the Glue Data Catalog for ETL operations.
Responsibilities:
Create, modify, and delete objects/tables in S3 buckets, including the raw, clean, curated zones, and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster).
Develop and execute Glue Jobs scripts for Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, ensuring efficient data transformation across the entire dataset in the Data Lake.
Determine appropriate actions, such as tokenization, to be applied in the raw zone for immediate data processing.
Set up dataset alarms to monitor the data pipeline and define notifications for missing data ingested.
Collaborate with stakeholders to determine data transformation requirements for selected datasets within the Data Lake.
Apply data standardization techniques in the clean zone to ensure consistent and reliable data quality.
Create snapshots in the clean zone to capture data at specific points in time for analysis and auditing purposes.

title: Data Engineer | Day Shift | Permanent WFH
summary:
Craft the Future of Hospitality Data and Be Your Best Self with Ordermentum!
As a Data Engineer at Ordermentum, you're not just joining a team; you're embarking on a transformative journey. Imagine having the opportunity to shape the future of the hospitality industry right from the comfort of your home, with a day shift that aligns perfectly with your work-life balance. At Ordermentum, we've redefined what it means to have a global position without ever leaving your country. Picture this: you'll be working with a diverse and dynamic team, collaborating with colleagues from across the globe to create a smarter, happier, and more sustainable hospitality industry.
Here, you won't find the typical nine-to-five grind. We value work-life balance and understand that your best work comes when you're at your best self. That's why we offer a day shift schedule that allows you to make the most of your personal and professional life. But that's not all. At Ordermentum, you'll immerse yourself in a culture of constant learning and growth. We embrace a philosophy of striving for win-wins, where your career progression is as important to us as it is to you. In this role, you'll have the chance to make an impact that reaches far beyond the borders of your country, contributing to the global success of a company that's always moving "Up and To The Right" in every way. Join us, and together, let's stay human as we craft a future where the hospitality industry thrives like never before.
Whom you’ll work with
Our client, Ordermentum, is a trailblazer in the food and beverage industry. They're on a mission to revolutionize how food and beverage companies manage orders, process payments, and discover innovative products and services that save both time and money. With a cutting-edge cloud-based B2B marketplace, Ordermentum powers the food and beverage industry in Australia, making it trade smarter. Since its inception in 2014, the company has grown exponentially, serving 37,000+ venues, 700+ suppliers, and processing over $2.5 billion in orders. Ordermentum has successfully addressed a common pain point in the hospitality industry: the complex and time-consuming ordering and payment process between suppliers and venues. Founded by industry experts Adam Theobald and Andrew Low, Ordermentum continues to evolve, bringing new features and innovations to the platform.
Job Description
Join our client's team as a Data Engineer, where you'll drive the transformation of the hospitality sector. You'll assist in extracting vital insights from data using SQL and Python, automating and optimizing processes. Your role extends to shaping the company's data vision, ensuring its reliability, and promoting best practices for data adoption. This position offers a unique opportunity to influence the industry, with responsibilities spanning project definition, execution, and data protection.
Here's an overview of your future role:
Employment type: Full-time
Shift: Day Shift (Mon - Fri 06:00 AM - 03:00 PM)
Work setup: Permanent WFH
What will your day-to-day tasks look like?
Help teams and stakeholders understand key insights from data analysis.
Utilize real-world data, primarily with SQL and Python, to automate and optimize data loading and transformation.
Proactively shape the technical vision for data across the business and execute plans to achieve it.
Ensure the high availability, reliability, and robustness of the data platform.
Define processes for operational excellence within the team.
Champion best data practices and drive data adoption for key decisions.
