title: Data Operations Analyst (Multiple Vacancies)
summary:
The Data Operations and Engineering (DOPE) division of Nasdaq Data Link is responsible for the datasets that our customers buy and consume every day.
As part of the Data Operations Team, you will contribute by managing and coordinating the onboarding process of products to Nasdaq Data Link. Coordinating various checklists and validation steps with the Product Owners and Product Managers. Organize and report the progress of partner and Nasdaq data sets through the process. Ensure completeness, accuracy, timeliness, and completeness of the processes managed.
What we offer
You can expect a collaborative and fast-paced work environment where you are recognized for your results and ability to drive things forward. Every day brings many opportunities to learn & grow!
In return, you will receive a great compensation package, HMO coverage for you and your dependents, annual bonus, employee stock purchase plan, retirement plan, mentorship, wellness subscription plans, tuition repayment or reimbursement options, paid vacation, and paid sick leave.
This is a permanent full-time role based in Bonifacio Global City, Taguig following a hybrid work arrangement and a night shift (US Eastern Time) schedule.
Our team's responsibilities
We lead ongoing prioritization of improvements, data collection, and distribution including supervising the operational delivery of the service to clients and works with sales and marketing to ensure alignment of go-to-market strategy. Our team serves as the primary point of contact with clients and ensure client satisfaction.
Your day-to-day:
Work with partners to onboard their products and related materials to Data Link
Report back to Partner and product owners the status of partners in their onboarding process
Assist the various support teams to resolve outstanding queries from customers
Work with Product team to automate the data onboarding process and establish processes to perform checks throughout the process
Work with various groups to ensure updated documentation on data products and work with partners to ensure materials are updated.
Ability to:
Proactively identify and solve problems and incidents of all types
Analyze large data sets and transform data into unique insights
Handle multiple assignments at once and meet associated deadlines important to success
Work both independently as well as collaborate on a team
What we’re looking for:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Finance, Economics, Mathematics, or equivalent qualification in a related field highly preferred
Have a working knowledge of SQL
At least two (2) years of proven experience, preferably in a similar organization
A strong grasp of the financial services industry
Able to communicate professionally with internal and external stakeholders
Experience working with financial data (preferred)
Superior level of attention to detail
Eager to learn about new data services and continuously improve processes
Beneficial skills (not required):
Knowledge in Python
Knowledge of Docker and Git
Familiarity with Airflow, Databricks, Amazon S3 and JIRA

In this role, the successful candidate will collaborate closely with our talented team of Project Managers, Digital Transformation Leaders, Data Scientists, Software Engineers, and healthcare domain experts to translate business challenges into innovative AI-driven solutions. Possessing an end-to-end perspective, you will navigate projects from their conceptualization to full-scale deployment, while ensuring data privacy and regulatory compliance, which will be crucial in delivering successful outcomes that positively impact patient care and operational efficiency
Responsibilities:
Digital Transformation Strategy: Collaborate with key stakeholders and business leaders to understand business objectives and challenges. Develop digital transformation strategies that leverage Machine Learning, NLP, Generative AI, and other AI technologies to address specific healthcare industry needs.
Architecture Design: Design end-to-end solutions architecture that aligns with the organization's digital transformation vision. Develop detailed technical designs, ensuring scalability, security, and integration with existing systems.
Machine Learning and AI Expertise: Provide in-depth expertise in Machine Learning, NLP, Generative AI, and other AI-related fields. Evaluate, select, and integrate relevant AI technologies to enhance healthcare processes, decision-making, and patient care.
Project Management: Lead the planning, execution, and delivery of digital transformation projects. Manage project timelines, resources, and risks to ensure successful deployment and implementation of AI solutions.
Healthcare Domain Knowledge: Leverage your extensive healthcare industry knowledge to understand regulatory requirements, compliance standards, and patient privacy concerns. Translate healthcare challenges into actionable technology solutions.
Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams, including Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Software Developers, and healthcare domain experts. Foster a collaborative and innovative environment to achieve project goals.
Technical Evaluation: Evaluate emerging AI technologies, tools, and frameworks relevant to healthcare applications. Recommend and implement improvements to existing solutions to enhance performance and efficiency.
Documentation: Prepare comprehensive technical documentation, including architecture diagrams, design specifications, and implementation guidelines
Additional Responsibilities:
1.    Conversational AI Design: Lead the design and implementation of Conversational AI solutions, including chatbots and virtual assistants, to enhance user interactions and improve customer experiences in the healthcare domain
2.    Intelligent Document Processing: Architect solutions for Intelligent Document Processing (IDP) to automate the extraction of information from unstructured documents, such as medical records, reports, and forms.
3.    Proof of Concept (PoC) Development: Lead the development of PoCs to demonstrate the feasibility and potential of AI technologies in addressing specific healthcare challenges. Collaborate with stakeholders to gather feedback and iterate on the PoC to validate its efficacy
4.    Industry Trends and Innovation: Stay abreast of the latest trends and advancements in Machine Learning, NLP, Generative AI, and healthcare technology. Propose innovative solutions to address emerging challenges and opportunities
5.    Stakeholder Education: Educate and collaborate with key stakeholders, including executives, project sponsors, and healthcare professionals, to build awareness and understanding of AI technologies' potential impact on healthcare processes and patient outcomes
6.    Clinical Decision Support: Collaborate with healthcare professionals and data scientists to design and deploy AI-powered clinical decision support systems, assisting medical staff in diagnosing and treating patients
Organizational Relationships
Reports To : AVP – Digital Transformation & Solutioning  Supervises : N/A

summary:
Unleash Your Data Genius: Join Us as a Data Scientist in Healthcare Analytics!
Imagine a career where you can truly have it all—global opportunities without leaving your country or even your home, a work-life balance that's more than just a promise, and a chance to make waves in healthcare analytics. Bachelor’s degree in a technical field or equivalent work experience.
Minimum of 3 years of relevant professional experience, including the healthcare or life sciences industry.
Proficiency in data science technologies, including legacy SAS code.
Advanced programming skills, with a focus on SQL.
Deep understanding of Medical Claims data and medical coding systems.
Ability to work independently, analyze data, and build programs.
Excellent critical thinking, time management, and communication skills.
Inquisitive self-starter with a passion for growth and learning.
What awaits you in this role?
Turn medical claims data into measures and actionable insights within our Software as a Service (SaaS) solutions.
Utilize your strong quantitative analysis skills, along with Python, SAS, and SQL proficiency, to create and analyze scripts for computing metrics and impacting downstream data sets.

title: Database Developer
summary:
JOB DESCRIPTION:
As a Database Developer, you will be crucial in designing, developing, and maintaining efficient and secure databases that support an organization's data management needs. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams, including software developers, data analysts, and system administrators, to ensure data integrity, performance, and reliability. This position requires a deep understanding of database technologies, strong analytical skills, and a passion for developing and optimizing data storage and retrieval processes.    
JOB RESPONSIBILITIES:
Database Design and Development:
Analyze and understand business requirements to design, develop, and implement appropriate database solutions.
Create and optimize database schemas, tables, views, and stored procedures for efficient data storage and retrieval.
Collaborate with software developers to integrate database components into applications, ensuring seamless functionality.
Data Modeling and Optimization:
Develop and maintain data models representing the organization's data structure and relationships.
Identify and implement performance optimization techniques like indexing, query optimization, and caching mechanisms.
Monitor and analyze database performance metrics to identify bottlenecks and recommend improvements.
Database Administration:
Install, configure, and upgrade database management systems (DBMS) and associated tools.
Monitor database systems to ensure optimal performance, availability, and reliability.
Troubleshoot and resolve database-related issues, including performance bottlenecks, data corruption, and system failures.
Collaboration and Documentation:
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather requirements, provide technical guidance, and support data-related initiatives.
Document database designs, configurations, and troubleshooting procedures for future reference.
Stay updated with emerging trends and technologies in database management and propose innovative solutions to enhance data management processes.
JOB REQUIREMENTS:
Minimum Requirements:
Must be able to read, write and modify complex SQL queries.
Proven experience working as a Database Developer or in a similar role.
Strong knowledge and proficiency in SQL, NoSQL, relational database, and Data Warehouse management systems (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, BigQuery, etc.).
Familiarity with data modeling and database design principles.
Basic understanding of performance tuning, query optimization, and troubleshooting common database issues.
Good problem-solving and analytical skills.
Effective communication and collaboration skills to work within cross-functional teams.
Ability to handle multiple tasks and prioritize effectively in a fast-paced environment.
Desired Skills:
Good understanding of, or preferably ITIL Foundation certified. Database certifications are a plus.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills, customer focus, and ability to work with both technical and non-technical people.
Strong attention to detail and analytical thinking in resolving problems and documenting solutions.
Ability to work proactively, independently, and as part of a team, supporting other team members when required.
Skills:
Designing database structures and tables
Data Modeling
Creating database automation
Optimizing SQL queries to integrate with applications
Developing functions, views, and stored procedures  
Excellent understanding of database principles, structures, theories, and practices
Strong SQL development skills

Accenture is a leading global professional services company that helps the world’s leading businesses, governments and other organizations build their digital core, optimize their operations, accelerate revenue growth and enhance citizen services—creating tangible value at speed and scale. We are a talent and innovation led company with 732,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries. We are uniquely able to deliver tangible outcomes because of our broad range of services, solutions and assets across Strategy & Consulting, Technology, Operations, Industry X and Accenture Song. These capabilities, together with our culture of shared success and commitment to creating 360° value, enable us to help our clients succeed and build trusted, lasting relationships. We measure our success by the 360° value we create for our clients, each other, our shareholders, partners and communities.
The Work:

 Bachelor's Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or other related fields.

summary:

Discover a world of endless possibilities with Cambridge University Press & Assessment, a distinguished global academic publisher and assessment organisation proudly affiliated with the prestigious University of Cambridge.
We are looking for a DevOps Engineer, a Senior Software Engineer by discipline, who will be part of a small, cross-functional Data Engineering Team with a focus on connecting an ecosystem of microservices. The role will help the business make data driven decisions and centralise domains and put value at the fingertips of the entire organization.
Why Cambridge?
At Cambridge, our unwavering commitment is to excel in education, learning, and research on a global scale. With a presence in over 170 countries, we empower millions of individuals, unlocking their potential and enabling their success. From dedicated teachers shaping young minds to visionary researchers pushing the boundaries of knowledge, we embody a relentless pursuit of enlightenment, curiosity, and understanding.
We embrace change as an opportunity for growth and progress, constantly adapting to meet the evolving needs of our customers. Collaboration and attentive listening are at the heart of our journey, as we work hand in hand with our customers and each other to innovate and discover more effective ways to achieve our goals. We believe people thrive in an environment where Trust and Empowerment are at the forefront, which is why all our new team members are provided regularisation on their first day so they can start #PursuingPotential from day one.
Joining Cambridge means becoming a part of an extraordinary institution renowned worldwide. Beyond that, you'll become a part of a vibrant and forward-thinking community that transcends tradition, fostering a culture of continuous growth and personal development. Here, we provide the perfect environment for you to thrive, supporting your professional journey and empowering you to reach your highest potential.
What can you get from Cambridge?
In this role, you'll have the opportunity to collaborate with colleagues from diverse branches, expanding your horizons and enriching your understanding of different cultures. We value your wellbeing and offer stability, fostering your professional and personal growth through internal and external activities and training sessions to help enrich your skillset.
Enjoy work-life balance flexibility through our range of options, including flexible schedules, hybrid work arrangements, and generous paid leave. As a regular employee on Day One, you'll have access to comprehensive healthcare benefits, ensuring your peace of mind with coverage for dependents, group life insurance, and robust well-being programs.
What makes you the ideal candidate in this role?
You will report to Lead Data Engineer and Data Architect in planning and designing the streaming platform. You will collaborate with other developers in designing and deploying applications and data streaming pipeline, and with data engineers in processing the data needed for a downstream data warehouse. Specifically; you will be a contributor to the design, will write codes, and be a first pass at the problem. You will plan your own data modelling and design projects.
Your responsibility will be to support the design, development, governance, operation, security, and maintenance of the English data streaming platform, data pipeline and infrastructure, and data stores. You will facilitate input from stakeholders, provide constructive challenges, enable effective prioritisation of requirements, and make critical choices independently such as delivering platform components to deliver value. You will also take initiative to advance your own skills, and identify and manage development opportunities in the area of your responsibility.
The following will help you be an ideal candidate for this post:
You have 3 – 5 years of proven web developer experience, ideally with ability to developer software from scratch and deploy to cloud platform with ease.
Proficiency in either Typescript or Javascript, with backend (NodeJS/Express/Nest.js) and front-end (Vue/React/Angular/NuxtJS) experience, has a strong grasp of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), different web rendering technologies such as SPA, MPA and SSR, and testing framework (Jest/Mocha/Chai)
Extensive software engineering experience with DevOps and CICD such as Terraform/CloudFormation, CDK, and GitHub, version control systems such as Git, RESTful APIs and HTTP protocols.
Experience of cloud and serverless computing (AWS), event streaming (Confluent Cloud/Apache Kafka) and container technologies such as Kubernetes/Docker; background in Unix/Linux.
Working experience with Kanban or SCRUM and a good understanding of data security best practices.
If you are driven to build data streaming platform using modern Big data tools in the cloud, and desire to be part of a globally renowned institution that celebrates innovation, embraces inclusion, and empowers learners, we invite you to pursue your potential with us.
Benefits & Others: Dental, Medical, Vision, Vesting Plan (Early Retirement), Hybrid/Flexible work arrangements, Trainings, Business Casual, Flexible Schedule

title: Lead Database Developer | SQL
summary:
Emerson’s 132 years of history have been filled with achievements and challenges that have driven innovative thinking and bold transformations, molding us into the company we are today. By joining us as a Lead Database Developer, Custom Applications, you will primarily be responsible for revolving around designing, developing, and maintaining robust database solutions that support business applications. You will guide and mentor other developers and devise strategies to improve team processes and practices.
In this capacity, you will play a pivotal role in driving innovation and excellence within our organization as a leader in shaping database solutions. You will conduct reviews, stay updated on industry trends, and optimize data integrity and performance. You will gather requirements, translate them into efficient designs, and maintain documentation for seamless deployment. This gives you a very vital role in helping drive growth platforms and supporting operational pillars while striving for long-term value creation.
If this sounds like a perfect fit for you, apply now and join our team in Quezon City, Philippines! All roles are currently on a blended Work-From-Home arrangement, and company-provided IT assets are given on your first day. Enjoy our market-competitive pay, comprehensive benefits package, well-being programs, and career development opportunities.
In this role, you will:
Design, develop, and maintain robust and scalable database solutions that support business applications.
Collaborate closely with application developers, designers, and product managers to ensure the successful delivery of high-quality database solutions.
Provide leadership and mentorship to a team of developers, guiding their professional growth and promoting best practices.
Identify and implement strategies to improve processes and practices related to database development, enhancing efficiency and productivity.
Ensure data integrity, security, and performance optimization in all database solutions, conducting regular code reviews and providing constructive feedback.
For this role, you will need:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Technology, Information Systems, or related courses.
8–10 years of relevant work experience in the database design and development field using any standard SQL database.
Strong knowledge and experience in database structure systems.
Strong technical background in database development, including proficiency in SQL, database management systems, database development tools, performance tuning, and troubleshooting.
Excellent organizational and analytical skills and the ability to analyze complex data and make recommendations based on findings.
Who you are: 
You have a strong drive for results and exhibit passion and enthusiasm to get things done. With excellent analytical and quantitative skills, you can efficiently carry out tasks independently and generate accurate, high-quality reports. You are proactive and highly innovative in approaching problem-solving efficiently. With good communication skills, you can proficiently communicate ideas and influence both internal and external customers. You're interpersonally savvy and able to collaborate and efficiently work with people at any level.
Benefits & Others: Dental, Education support, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Loans, Well-Being Days, Counseling Service, Fund Assistance, Business Casual, Shifting Schedule

title: Senior Product Manager
summary:
Who We Are
STRATPOINT accelerates the digital transformation of businesses, delivering enterprise-grade solutions globally for more than 20 years. We specialize in agile software development, quality assurance, cloud, data engineering, and AI.
Our C.A.R.E. values:
nourish Creativity
embody Agility
manifest Reliability
pursue Evolution
The Role
At Stratpoint, we know that creating outstanding software products and customer experiences (CX) are a significant part of executing a company’s digital strategy. That’s why we are looking for a qualified Head of Product to lead our product development strategy and execution.
As Head of Product, you will drive product strategy, road mapping, and execution across the organization, build our product management and customer experience practice, and work with our business units to create new digital products.
The ideal candidate will be experienced in 0-1 product launches and can be trusted to dive right into internal product initiatives as well as client projects, ensuring that our applications not only meet customer needs but also deliver outstanding experiences.
The Benefits
At Stratpoint, we enjoy the autonomy, lack of bureaucracy, and the freedom to experiment but without the chaos. We’re like a startup but with adult supervision.
You will be supported by capable management of HR, Finance and IT that adheres to the highest standards of integrity and good governance.
Hybrid is our mode of work, but when we need to come together, we have inviting open floor office spaces designed to spark gatherings, collaboration, and camaraderie.
Stratpoint employees enjoy: 
SSS, Pag-ibig and Philhealth benefits + company contribution
a monthly miscellaneous allowance 
13th month pay based on your monthly rate. 
Vacation and Sick leave
Wellness programs such as Wellness Wednesdays 
HMO coverage 
Team buildings and quarterly events (company outings and festive celebrations for Chinese New Year, Valentines, Halloween and Christmas)
And, friendly intramural competitions
As a senior leader, your high performance is rewarded with a combination of stock options and performance bonuses.
Your Responsibilities:
Develop and execute a product strategy and roadmap that integrates customer experience (CX) design aligned to the company’s goals
Build our product management and customer experience capability by leading our community of product owners, business analysts and UX designers
Oversee the entire product development lifecycle, from discovery to product launch, ensuring a strong focus on delivering exceptional user experiences.
Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including engineering, design, marketing, and sales, to ensure alignment and successful product delivery while maintaining a strong focus on CX
Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) related to CX and regularly monitor product performance against these metrics, making adjustments as needed.
Perform additional assignments as directed by the Senior Management.
About You:
You are/have:
A Bachelor's/College Degree in Business, Marketing, Design, or related field
Proven experience in product management or related roles, with a track record of successfully delivering products that prioritize CX
Strong presentation and communications skills to C-level clients to lead customer discussions
Proficiency in using product management and CX design tools and software
Experience with Design Thinking, Agile, and Scrum methodologies
Cross-collaboration enthusiast; able and willing to utilize internal resources to meet project deadlines and objectives
Solid business acumen with a keen sense of urgency
Demonstrated strategic thinking with proven ability to execute against tight deadlines and drive multiple projects at once
At least 7+ years of experience in product roles
The requirements listed in this job description are guidelines, not hard and fast rules. You don’t have to satisfy every requirement or meet every qualification listed. If your skills are transferable and you are in the ballpark of what we are looking for, we encourage you to submit an application.
We look forward to getting to know you more!
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Business (e.g. Shirts), Employee Stock Option

title: Data Integrations Analyst
summary:
This position is within Acadia. Acadia is wholly owned by LSEG (London Stock Exchange Group) and is part of its Post Trade division.
Data Integrations forms part of the Client Services team responsible for implementing solutions to onboard counterparties on proprietary software, at the same time delivering technical application support to clients globally 24x6.
Job Highlights
This position is eligible for flexible work arrangement – remote or hybrid
Night shift (US hours)
Training 2-3 months APAC or EMEA shift
Flexibility required to cover non-US shifts regularly
Role Responsibilities
Work with technical onboarding of new clients onto the proprietary MarginSphere software application.
Work closely on the implementation of additional services for existing clients.
Configuration of Business Rules Engine (BRE) for ETL.
Resolution of escalated support issue.
Ensure that the highest levels of service are delivered to AcadiaSoft clients.
Provide telephone and email-based customer support.
Experience and Qualifications Required
1-3 years of programming experience preferred – open to new college graduates
Bachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent
Excellent communication skills (written and verbal)
Ability to use/understand SQL queries
Must be familiar with Source control (Git, etc.)
Must be familiar with Issue tracking (Jira, etc.)
Eager to learn, capable of understanding concepts and applying them to novel scenarios
Excellent technical troubleshooting/critical thinking skills
Experience or training in direct customer-facing role is a plus
Ability to effectively handle competing priorities in a fluid environment
Experience working multiple small to medium-sized projects simultaneously is a plus
Must be familiar with XML and/or JSON structures is a plus
Exposure to financial markets, particularly the collateral/derivatives and risk management space is a plus
We believe that creating a diverse and inclusive organisation is fundamental to the way we deliver on our promise of creating essential partnerships and open opportunities. Our open culture is central to how we deliver our purpose - driving financial stability, empowering economies and enabling customers to create sustainable growth - in everything we do.
Working with us means that you will be part of a dynamic organisation of 25,000 people across 70 countries. However, we will value your individuality and enable you to bring your true self to work so you can help enrich our diverse workforce. You will be part of a collaborative and creative culture where we encourage new ideas and are committed to sustainability across our global business. You will experience the critical role we have in helping to re-engineer the financial ecosystem to support and drive sustainable economic growth. title: Integration Manager
summary:

title: Sales Director
summary:
Who We Are
STRATPOINT accelerates the digital transformation of businesses, delivering enterprise-grade solutions globally for more than 20 years. We specialize in agile software development, quality assurance, cloud, data engineering, and AI.
Our C.A.R.E. values:
nourish Creativity
embody Agility
manifest Reliability
pursue Evolution
The Role
At Stratpoint, we’re aware that continued business growth and relevance requires companies to invest in their digital acceleration and it is our mission to help organizations execute on their digital strategy. That’s why we are looking for a qualified Sales Director.
You will grow and lead a highly motivated sales team to manage and expand our accounts in the Philippines and extend our reach to untapped business opportunities in the US and other foreign markets. Some travel may be needed for this role for events, conferences, and client meetings.
You will be trusted to dive right into a customer-centric/consultative selling approach, learn the ins-and-outs of the company, and foster relationships with key clients and partners to drive significant revenue. You will join our senior leadership team to develop and execute strategies to scale at speed to make a significant impact in building the software infrastructure of businesses
The Benefits
At Stratpoint, we enjoy the autonomy, lack of bureaucracy, and the freedom to experiment but without the chaos. We’re like a startup but with adult supervision.
You will be supported by capable management of HR, Finance and IT that adheres to the highest standards of integrity and good governance.
Hybrid is our mode of work, but when we need to come together, we have inviting open floor office spaces designed to spark gatherings, collaboration, and camaraderie.
Stratpoint employees enjoy: 
SSS, Pag-ibig, and Philhealth benefits + company contribution
a monthly miscellaneous allowance 
13th-month pay based on your monthly rate. 
Vacation and Sick leave
Wellness programs such as Wellness Wednesdays 
HMO coverage 
Team buildings and quarterly events (company outings and festive celebrations for Chinese New Year, Valentines, Halloween and Christmas)
And, friendly intramural competitions
As a senior leader, your high performance is rewarded with a combination of stock options and performance bonuses
Your Team
You will lead and elevate a team of sales professionals (account managers, business development managers, sales development representatives) to support our rapidly growing company as we continue to expand internationally.
You will report directly to the CEO. Your other key stakeholders are the senior management team— business unit heads and marketing director.  
You will work closely with our business partners, the biggest brands in technology, such as Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud, Microsoft and Outsystems, to develop and execute joint GTM strategies.
Your Responsibilities:
Evaluate, develop, and execute sales strategies to meet or exceed the company’s target sales volume.
Build and nurture relationships with key client accounts through consultative selling and providing a high level of customer experience.
Recruit, manage, and mentor a highly performing sales team of account managers and business development managers to confidently manage a healthy and strong sales pipeline from generating their own leads to closing deals.
Monitor sales metrics, track progress, and make data-driven decisions and recommendations to optimize sales performance.
Keep abreast of industry trends and customer drivers to share with business unit managers, marketing, and other stakeholders to adapt strategies accordingly.
Collaborate with other departments such as marketing, business units, and HR to align efforts and achieve company goals.
Nurture, develop, and explore new business opportunities.
Develop and deliver sales training programs to ensure the team is equipped with the necessary skills and knowledge.
Conduct regular performance evaluations for the sales team, provide feedback, and implement improvement plans when needed.
Perform additional assignments as directed by the CEO/Senior Management.
About You:
You are/have:
A Bachelor's/College Degree in Business, Marketing, or related field
Proven experience in a senior sales leadership role, preferably in B2B technology selling for enterprise accounts
A Helper – you like to help people solve their problems and reach their goals
Strong presentation and communications skills to C-level clients to lead customer discussions
Proficient in data analysis, forecasting, and budgeting
Experience with CRM and sales engagement tools (i.e., Salesforce, Hubspot, etc)
Cross-collaboration enthusiast; able and willing to utilize internal resources to meet project deadlines and objectives
Solid business acumen with a keen sense of urgency
Demonstrated strategic thinking with proven ability to execute against tight deadlines and drive multiple projects at once
At least 10+ years experience in Sales
The requirements listed in this job description are guidelines, not hard and fast rules. You don’t have to satisfy every requirement or meet every qualification listed. If your skills are transferable and you are in the ballpark of what we are looking for, we encourage you to submit an application.
We look forward to getting to know you more!
Benefits & Others: Dental, Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Regular hours, Mondays - Fridays, Business (e.g. Shirts), Employee Stock Option

Work internally with the IT team, software engineers, product managers, data engineers, internal auditors, and external auditors/regulators to identify any control gaps in IT environment, and implement all of the ITGC’s that are required under Sarbanes-Oxley (SOX) and HIPAA/HITECH

Document, update, & enhance the Enterprise Technology Policies to ensure that the policies contain all of the required IT Controls, and that the policies accurately reflect the processes & procedures that are employed by client personnel.
Support the IT & Engineering teams in identifying ways to increase compliance automation
Design, implement, & perform periodic lookback procedures to help ensure that IT Controls that are related to Change Management, Incident Management, and User Access Management are designed & operating effectively.

Our purpose
Here at Datacom, we connect people and technology in order to solve challenges, create opportunities, and discover new possibilities for the communities we live in
The Nitty Gritty
Datacom is Australasia's largest homegrown technology services business of over 6500 people, from humble beginnings as a small family business, we have enjoyed healthy, organic, and sustainable growth to become a large multinational, that proudly holds on to our ‘small family business feel.
We have extensive expertise in operating data centers, providing IT services, software engineering, and application management, as well as payroll and customer service design and operations. With this comes a long list of significant clients Datacom is committed to hiring, developing, and promoting the best talent from a diverse range of backgrounds. We are local at heart, yet world-class in capability.
At the center of our vision and values are people: our people. We are guided by what is best for our staff, our customers, and our communities.
Growing to dominate the New Zealand government and corporate IT market, we expanded into the Philippines, Malaysia, and Australia in the mid-90s and have been growing in those regions ever since.
Do you have what it takes to help us grow? This is your chance to be part of something new, getting on from the ‘ground floor’ and benefiting from all the up-side of a ‘start-up’ initiative with the security of a large multinational (and yet none of the down-side).
Role Overview and Objectives
The accountant will monitor, prepare and maintain financial information, and reporting in accordance with best practice. The accountant is responsible for supporting senior accountants and members of the shared service team with accounting duties including monitoring transactions, resolving queries, and assisting with analysis. Role Responsibilities
The accountant is responsible for (but not limited to):
Record-2-Report activities.
Assisting in the generation of general ledger transactions and subsequent related adjustments.
Supporting monthly activities including balance sheet reconciliations.
Supporting the preparation of financial analysis and reports from a profit and loss and balance sheet perspective.
Supporting the analysis and review of financial information of discrepancies and variances.
Contributing to the development of new or amended accounting systems, programs, and procedures including initiating any actions to reduce write-offs and improve efficiencies.
Assisting audit preparations and year-end activities.
Supporting the preparation of accounting records and financial reports as per Datacom standards.
Ensuring all accounting tasks are completed within the set timeframe and any issues addressed as they arise.
Liaising with the broader team to ensure that all reporting standards are appropriately embedded into relevant finance processes.
Performing other accounting duties and supporting the broader team as required or assigned.
Supporting the design and implementation of effective and appropriate financial controls.
Requirements
Knowledge
Detailed knowledge of general accounting systems, processes, and practices.
Strong technical accounting ability.
Working knowledge of Oracle or a similar-sized ERP system.
Experience
3-5 years of general accounting or audit experience.
Experience influencing stakeholders through challenging situations.
Previous involvement in the implementation of a new accounting system or management and evolution of an existing system
Experience working either within Datacom or for a similar-sized organization.
Skills
Expertise in MS Excel and the ability to create models and reports using Pivot Table is a MUST
Previous exposure to payroll-related accounting is quite critical.
AU or NZ Payroll Accounting experience is a MUST
Experience with AU and/or NZ payroll experience or knowledge and a good understanding of NZ/AU payroll-related tax rules (i.e. accounting of salaries, superannuation, PAYE/G, payroll tax, etc.).
Ability to deliver accurate and timely financial outputs.
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to build relationships with people at any level in the organization.
Excellent organizational skills
Passion for process improvement and simplification
Strong system skills, including proficiency with Microsoft Office applications and enterprise resource planning software (ERP).
Certification
Certified Public Accountant is highly desirable
Benefits

Able to work independently as well as be collaborative and a team player
Excellent customer service and communication skills
Ability to cope with multiple tasks and initiatives
Intellectual curiosity and dedicated to keeping up with advances in analytics tools and approaches

title: SURVEYOR (Construction)
summary:
Job Description:
As a Surveyor, your primary responsibility will be to perform land surveying and geodetic engineering tasks to collect, analyze, and interpret spatial data. You will play a vital role in measuring and mapping the Earth's surface, providing accurate survey information for various engineering, construction, and land development projects.
Responsibilities:
Survey Planning and Design: Collaborate with project managers and stakeholders to understand survey requirements and objectives. Develop survey plans, strategies, and methodologies to ensure accurate data collection and efficient project execution.
Field Data Collection: Conduct field surveys using advanced surveying instruments, such as total stations, GPS receivers, and laser scanners. Use traditional and digital surveying techniques to measure and record data related to land boundaries, topography, structures, and infrastructure.
Data Processing and Analysis: Process survey data using specialized software and computer-aided design (CAD) tools. Perform data adjustment, transformation, and geospatial analysis to generate accurate maps, plans, and digital models.
Land Boundary Determination: Conduct boundary surveys to establish and demarcate property lines and legal boundaries. Research property deeds, historical records, and relevant legal documents to ensure accurate land boundary identification.
Geodetic Control Network: Establish and maintain geodetic control points to ensure accurate positioning and reference framework for surveying activities. Perform network adjustment and data integration to align survey data with national or regional coordinate systems.
Mapping and Plan Preparation: Prepare survey maps, plans, and reports based on collected data and analysis. Ensure compliance with survey standards, regulations, and client specifications. Generate accurate and detailed deliverables for engineering design, construction, and land management purposes.
Construction and Infrastructure Surveys: Conduct construction surveys to provide accurate layout and staking for infrastructure projects, including roads, buildings, pipelines, and utilities. Monitor and verify construction activities to ensure compliance with design specifications.
Data Quality Assurance: Implement quality control measures to ensure the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of survey data and deliverables. Perform data validation, error detection, and correction procedures to maintain data integrity.
Client Communication and Collaboration: Interact with clients, project stakeholders, and regulatory authorities to understand project requirements, address concerns, and provide technical expertise. Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams, including engineers, architects, and construction professionals, to support project coordination and decision-making.
Professional Development: Stay updated with the latest surveying techniques, technologies, and industry best practices. Pursue continuing education opportunities and professional certifications to enhance skills and maintain professional competency.
Requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Geodetic Engineering, Surveying, or a related field. Professional licensure or certification as a Surveyor/Geodetic Engineer is required.
Proven experience in land surveying, geodetic engineering, or related surveying disciplines.
Proficiency in using surveying instruments, such as total stations, GPS receivers, and laser scanners.
Strong knowledge of surveying principles, geodetic datums, coordinate systems, and mapping techniques.
Familiarity with surveying software and CAD tools for data processing, analysis, and plan preparation.
Understanding of legal and regulatory requirements related to land boundaries and surveying.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with attention to detail and accuracy.
Proficient in using GIS (Geographic Information System) software and spatial data analysis tools.
Strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively in a team environment.
Ability to work in outdoor environments and travel to various project sites as required.
Strong organizational and time management skills to meet project deadlines and manage multiple surveying tasks simultaneously.
Willing to be assigned in provincial sites (CDO, Palawan).
CAN START ASAP!!!
Qualification: Bachelor's/College Degree, Professional License (Passed Board/Bar/Professional License Exam)
Benefits & Others: Miscellaneous allowance, Medical, Loans, Casual, Regular hours, Mondays-Fridays / half day during Saturday

summary:
Job Summary:
As the Product Support Tier 1 Team Lead, you will be responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the Tier 1 Product Support team. Your primary focus will be to ensure the successful delivery of high-quality support for internal users and external clients on a 24/7 basis via either support tickets or the support hotline. You will lead a team of 12x Tier 1 Support Analysts by providing guidance, mentoring, and fostering a collaborative environment to maximize team performance and customer satisfaction. Additionally, you will collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Tier 2 Support, Data Science, Product Engineering and Customer Success teams to drive continuous improvement and enhance the overall Support operation.  This role will be reporting to the Product Support Tier 1 Manager (Singapore-based) and a dotted line to the Site Operations Lead (Manila-based)

Lead and manage a team of 12x Tier 1 Support Analysts by providing guidance, support, and mentorship.
Set clear expectations, establish goals, and monitor team performance to ensure service levels and quality standards are consistently met.
Foster a positive and collaborative team environment, promoting professional development and knowledge sharing.

Product Support:
Oversee the progress of the team’s current Support tickets (via Zendesk) and Engineering/Data Science Escalations (via JIRA) to ensure timely and effective resolution.
Handle incoming Support tickets and demonstrate the ability to address complex issues on the platform
Lead by example and act as a mentor and provide oversight, coaching, and training to the team
On-board all-new Tier 1 Support Analyst team members
Maintaining and updating technical documents such as standard operating procedures/ playbooks.
Act as the primary point of contact for escalations, ensuring timely and satisfactory resolution of issues.
Conducting bi-weekly 1:1 with team members to discuss performance and goals
Conducting weekly team audits
Preparing monthly and quarterly reports on the team’s agreed goal, metrics and KPIs to the management team.
Process Improvement:
Identify opportunities for process improvement within the support function, proposing and implementing changes to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.
Work closely with cross-functional teams to streamline support processes, automate repetitive tasks, and optimize incident response and resolution times.
Implement and monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure team performance and drive continuous improvement.
Qualifications:
Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's/College degree in Information Technology
Proven experience in a similar role (3-5 years), leading a team of Application Support Analysts.
Strong technical background with expertise in troubleshooting, diagnosing, and resolving Application/SaaS issues.
Solid understanding of ITIL principles and experience with IT service management processes.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to effectively collaborate with technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Strong leadership and mentoring abilities, with a track record of building and motivating high-performing teams.
Critical thinking mindset, with the ability to analyze complex problems and develop practical solutions.
Experience in process improvement and driving operational efficiencies.
Experience with the Zendesk, JIRA, or Confluence software is a plus.

title: Senior Integration Engineer
summary:
NOTE: When you click the apply button, you will be re-directed to Cambridge University Press & Assessment’s website where you will be required to create a profile and upload a copy of your CV to complete your application.
We are Cambridge University Press & Assessment, a world-leading academic publisher and assessment organisation, and a proud part of the University of Cambridge. 
We are recruiting for a Senior Integration Engineer who will be part of our central Data & Integration team. In this role, you would design, build and maintain re-usable APIs and interfaces, primarily on the Mulesoft platform, and help developers across the organisation achieve success on this platform.  
You would get exposure to our Integration platforms (Mulesoft Anypoint and AWS Services) and help ensure best practices for integration engineering are up to date and adhered to, specifically with API-led Connectivity. Most importantly, you would help build our internal capability in this important area, upskilling/cross skilling and retaining talented individuals and helping them deliver effectively in empowered, agile squads.  
Why should you join Cambridge? 
Our mission is to contribute to society through the pursuit of education, learning, and research at the highest international levels of excellence. Which is why every year, we give vital support to millions of people in more than 170 countries around the world. From teachers and learners to researchers and academics, we help to build confidence, unlock potential, and enable success. We give people the opportunity to show what they've learnt, we spread knowledge, spark enquiry, and aid understanding. 
We achieve this by embracing change, and continuously focusing on our customers' needs. And by collaborating, and carefully listening to our customers and to each other, we keep moving forward, keep innovating, and keep finding newer and better ways of doing things. 
When you join Cambridge, you get the best possible combination of a supportive, caring environment, balanced with work that brings out the best in you. You will have access to learning and development opportunities, and business tools essential for your role so that you can perform at your peak.  
What can we offer you? 
In this role, you will collaborate with colleagues across different areas of the business and branches. It is an opportunity that will enable you to widen your horizon by learning from other cultures. 
The role is pivotal to the success of our Data Orchestration capability within the organization. There are no limits to the opportunities afforded to learn best practices in this field, work with new and exciting technologies, and collaborate with highly talented people. 
On top of these, working with Cambridge will also give you stability. We show our care for our people by allowing them to grow not just professionally but also personally. We promote work-life balance through flexible work schedules, hybrid work arrangements, and generous paid leaves. In addition, you will be entitled to our health care benefits with coverage for dependents, group life insurance, and robust wellbeing programs right on the first day of joining us.  
What will you do in this role? 
Technical Delivery within cross-functional squads. You will design, develop (hands–on), maintain and improve solutions that are developed both within and outside of the Data & Integration team. 
Technical leadership: You will work with your team and other practitioners to define & and adopt best practices for Orchestration / Integration. This means document and sharing skills, methods, tools, patterns and architectures required to level up and continually adapt and improve. 
Communications and relationship building: The role requires you to actively collaborate with a wide range of people across the organisation and ensure that timely and reliable information reaches everyone contributing to or impacted by the team's efforts. 
What makes you the ideal candidate for this position? 
You will be ideal for this role if you have hands-on experience with:
Developing REST APIs and are able to demonstrate both successful delivery and lessons learnt
Problem solving and fact-based decision making
Strong and broad understanding of API-led connectivity
Demonstrated leadership of technical teams
In addition, experience, knowledge or expertise in the following would give you an advantage: 
Creating API Specification using RAML / OAS in Anypoint Platform 
Implementing APIs in Mule 4 using Anypoint Studio, including manipulation using dataweave
High level of comfort with presenting and modeling data in JSON
Creating build and release pipelines for automated deployment
Good understanding of REST API Standards
Background in Java, Javascript
Background in SQL, NoSQL of any flavors
Background in GraphQL
Comfortable working in Agile methodology
Benefits & Others: Dental, Medical, Vision, Vesting Plan (Early Retirement), Hybrid/Flexible work arrangements, Trainings, Business Casual, Flexible Schedule

The Data Engineer will support our software developers, data analysts and the business stakeholders on data initiatives and will ensure optimal data delivery architecture is consistent throughout ongoing projects. They must be self-directed and comfortable supporting the data needs of multiple teams, systems and products. The right candidate will be excited by the prospect of optimizing or even re-designing our company’s data architecture to support our next generation of products and data initiatives. The Data Engineer will also create reports and dashboards as requested by business teams.
Key responsibilities include:
Create and maintain optimal data pipeline architecture
Assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional / non-functional business requirements.
Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability, etc.
Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading of data from a wide variety of data sources using SQL and AWS ‘big data’ technologies.
Build analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable insights into customer acquisition, operational efficiency and other key business performance metrics.
Work with stakeholders including the Executive, Product, Data and Design teams to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs.
Create data tools for analytics and data analyst that assist them in building and optimizing our product into an innovative industry leader.
Work with data and analyst to strive for greater functionality in our data systems.
Build reports and dashboards to support the data needs of business teams.
Key requirements include:
Advanced working SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases.
Experience building and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures and data sets.
Experience performing root cause analysis on internal and external data and processes to answer specific business questions and identify opportunities for improvement.
Strong analytic skills related to working with unstructured datasets.
Build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency and workload management.
A successful history of manipulating, processing and extracting value from large disconnected datasets.
Working knowledge of message queuing, stream processing, and highly scalable ‘big data’ data stores.
Experience supporting and working with cross-functional teams in a dynamic environment.
We are looking for a candidate with 5+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, who has attained a Graduate degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systems or another quantitative field. They should also have experience using the following software/tools:
Experience with big data tools
Experience with relational SQL and NoSQL databases, including Postgres, AWS Redshift and Dynamo DB
Experience with data pipeline and workflow management tools, including Airflow and Glue.
Experience with AWS cloud services: EC2, EMR, RDS, Redshift, DynamoDB, Airflow
Experience with stream-processing systems

title: ETL Developer
summary:
We are seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our team. As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for managing and optimizing data workflows within the AWS Console. Your primary focus will be on creating, modifying, and deleting objects/tables in S3 buckets, executing Glue Jobs scripts for ETL processes, and utilizing the Glue Data Catalog for ETL operations.
Responsibilities:
• Create, modify, and delete objects/tables in S3 buckets, including the raw, clean, curated zones, and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster).
• Develop and execute Glue Jobs scripts for Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, ensuring efficient data transformation across the entire dataset in the Data Lake.
• Determine appropriate actions, such as tokenization, to be applied in the raw zone for immediate data processing.
• Set up dataset alarms to monitor the data pipeline and define notifications for missing data ingested.
• Collaborate with stakeholders to determine data transformation requirements for selected datasets within the Data Lake.
• Apply data standardization techniques in the clean zone to ensure consistent and reliable data quality.
• Create snapshots in the clean zone to capture data at specific points in time for analysis and auditing purposes.
• Design and develop data models in the curated zone, optimizing data structures for efficient access and retrieval.
• Define tables/objects in the curated zone to support Salesforce usage, ensuring data integrity and compatibility.
• Identify and create tables/objects in the curated zone and the consumption layer (Redshift Cluster) for Tableau standard access.
• Determine tables/objects to be included in Redshift Spectrum for Tableau advanced access, enabling advanced data exploration and analysis.
• Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information technology, or a related field.
• Minimum of 3 years’ relevant work experience.
• Strong proficiency in working with the AWS Console, including S3, Glue, and Redshift services.
• Experience with ETL processes, scripting, and data transformation techniques.
• Familiarity with Glue Data Catalog and its usage in ETL workflows.
• Solid understanding of data lakes, data modeling, and database concepts.
• Ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and stakeholders.
• Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.
• Excellent communication and documentation skills.
• Attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high-quality results.
• Willing to travel and be deployed to client/affiliate off-shore (Hong Kong office).
If you are a self-motivated Data Engineer with a passion for working with AWS technologies and driving data-driven insights, we would love to hear from you. Join our dynamic team and contribute to the success of our affiliate's data initiatives.
Work Arrangement: Will be deployed in HK, and will be working in the HK Office. If he is here in the Philippines, he will be working from home.

title: Senior Manager, Data Science
company: Visa Philippines Business Processing Center, Corp.
summary:
Company Description
Visa is a world leader in digital payments, facilitating more than 215 billion payments transactions between consumers, merchants, financial institutions and government entities across more than 200 countries and territories each year. Our mission is to connect the world through the most innovative, convenient, reliable and secure payments network, enabling individuals, businesses and economies to thrive.
When you join Visa, you join a culture of purpose and belonging – where your growth is priority, your identity is embraced, and the work you do matters. We believe that economies that include everyone everywhere, uplift everyone everywhere. Your work will have a direct impact on billions of people around the world – helping unlock financial access to enable the future of money movement.
Join Visa: A Network Working for Everyone.
Job Description
Team Summary
Visa Consulting and Analytics (VCA) is Visa's consulting division, serving Visa's clients (including card issuers, acquirers and merchants) and solving their strategic problems focused on improving performance and profitability. Drawing on our expertise in strategy consulting, payments, data analytics, marketing, operational and macroeconomics, VCA drives high impact and tangible financial results.
The individual will be part of VCA Data Science geographic team cluster of Indonesia, Philippines, Vietnam, Myanmar and Cambodia (IPVMC) markets, and will be responsible for driving data science engagements with Visa's clients in Philippines and supporting end-to-end delivery. The team is involved in a comprehensive range of consulting services and solutions to our clients, that address unique challenges in areas such as strategic growth, profitability, risk management, digital strategy and portfolio management.
What a Data Science Senior Manager, Visa Consulting & Analytics does at Visa:
The Data Science Senior Manager will be a member of VCA Data Science team in Asia Pacific and will report to the Head of Data Science overseeing IPVMC cluster. The position will be based in Visa Philippines, Makati office.
The individual will be accountable for driving the design, development and implementation of analytics-driven strategies as well as high impact solutions for Visa clients. He/she will bring in a strong background in data science to solve complex problems in the domain of banking & payments , and unlock business value for Visa and its clients.
Key responsibilities include:
Define detailed scope of work and solution methodology, design and create data solutions and/or models using client data, Visa data or 3rd party data by leveraging appropriate tools and techniques
Clearly communicate data insights, findings and recommendations, drive deployment and implementation of solutions, as well as track impact
Ensure consistency, standards & quality control of data science work, with all project documentation up to date
Actively seek out opportunities to innovate and create new offerings by using data fit for purpose to the needs of our clients
Enhance existing data science techniques by promoting new methodologies and best practices in the field
Promote thought leadership in the data science domain and build intellectual property through innovation
Effectively interact with clients and manage internal/external stakeholder communication
Mentor, guide and supervise data scientists in the project team
Projects you will be a part of:
As part of VCA Data Science team, you will have the opportunity to work on strategically important projects for Visa and its clients. The scope of work may include, but is not limited to –
Working with issuer clients to assess opportunities using data across cardholder lifecycle, conduct gap assessment and provide recommendations for improvement
Business development and involvement in client pitches, to bring in strategic thinking that puts together a compelling proposition on data-driven solutions to help Visa win client projects and deepen partnerships
Build models/segmentation analysis/dashboard solutions and ensure clients find value to take action such as running marketing campaigns to drive payment card activation and usage, changing policies or processes, launching new products, opening new channels, among other things.
Provide thought leadership and analytics advisory to clients in the face of changing regulations and market landscape impacting business revenue streams
Why this is important to Visa
As payments consulting arm of Visa, VCA is growing a team of highly specialized experts who can provide best-in-class payment expertise and data-driven strategies to clients. We’re building a high-performing team of data scientists, data analysts and statisticians helping major organizations adapt and evolve to meet the changes taking place in technology, finance, and commerce, with cutting-edge, creative and advanced analytic solutions. The purpose of the team is to help Visa’s clients grow their business and solve problems by providing consulting services through the use of data. 
This is a hybrid position. Hybrid employees can alternate time between both remote and office. Employees in hybrid roles are expected to work from the office 2-3 set days a week (determined by leadership/site), with a general guidepost of being in the office 50% or more of the time based on business needs.
Qualifications
What you will need:
- Degree (Masters or Ph.D. would be an advantage) in Quantitative field such as Statistics, Mathematics, Operational Research, Computer Science, Economics, or engineering or equivalent experience
- Minimum 8-10 years of professional work experience in applying statistical solutions to business problems
- Hands on experience with data analytics/programming tools such as SAS/Salford SPM/Hadoop/R/SQL/Python/Hive, and a working knowledge of Hadoop ecosystem
- Proficiency in statistical techniques: Neural Networks, Gradient Boosting, Linear & Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forests, Markov Chains, Support Vector Machines, Clustering, Principal Component Analysis, Factor analysis, etc
- Demonstrated experience in planning, organizing, and managing multiple and concurrent analytics projects with diverse cross-functional stakeholders
- Strong internal team and external client stakeholder management with a collaborative, diplomatic, and flexible style, able to work effectively in a matrixed organization
- Strong presentation and storytelling skills, including strong oral and written capabilities
- Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the ability to progress on multiple priorities concurrently
- In-market experience and/or knowledge of local language, culture as well as industry regulations
What will also help:
- Strong understanding of payments and/or banking Industry including consumer credit, consumer debit, small business, commercial, co-brand and merchant
- Strong hold on MS Excel and PowerPoint
Additional Information
Visa is an EEO Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status. Visa will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with EEOC guidelines and applicable local law.

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience).
Proven experience (5+ years) working as a Site Reliability Engineer, Infrastructure Engineer, or similar roles, with a focus on data infrastructure and security.
Experience with real-time data processing technologies, such as Kafka and Debezium
Strong expertise in cloud technologies, particularly AWS and (HashiCorp nice to have).
Proficiency in Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform and Atlantis.
Experience with containerization and orchestration tools, particularly Kubernetes.
Solid understanding of bash/shell scripting and proficiency in at least one programming language.
Familiarity with CI/CD deployment pipelines and related tools.
Knowledge of HashiCorp products like Vault, Nomad, and Consul is a plus.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to troubleshoot complex systems.
Expertise in zero-trust architecture and service meshes is a plus
Experience with data-related technologies (databases, airflow, data warehousing, data lakes) is a plus.

title: Staff Data Engineer
summary:
Xendit provides payment infrastructure across Southeast Asia, with a focus on Indonesia, the Philippines and Malaysia. We process payments, power marketplaces, disburse payroll and loans, provide KYC solutions, prevent fraud, and help businesses grow exponentially. We serve our customers by providing a suite of world-class APIs, eCommerce platform integrations, and easy to use applications for individual entrepreneurs, SMEs, and enterprises alike.
Our main focus is building the most advanced payment rails for Southeast Asia, with a clear goal in mind — to make payments across and within SEA simple, secure and easy for everyone. We serve thousands of businesses ranging from SMEs to multinational enterprises, and process millions of transactions monthly. We’ve been growing rapidly since our inception in 2015, onboarding hundreds of new customers every month, and backed by global top-10 VCs. We’re proud to be featured on among the fastest growing companies by Y-Combinator.
About the Job
At Xendit, we seek a Senior/Staff Data engineer who will bring technical expertise to help us build a reliable and scalable Data platform to empower internal teams to work independently and unlock full potential of our data. You’ll bring a diverse set of skills across data engineering including data pipeline design at scale (batch/real-time), data infrastructure, data governance, data quality testing, development & deployment best practices, and more. You will be part of the Data engineering core team, working among 8 other talented data engineers. With your relentless drive for successful outcomes, you will work on the most complex projects within the core team as well as contribute to highly impactful cross-team initiatives. You can expect to own a technical roadmap ensuring the tools and services that the team provides are reliable, scalable, easy-to-use, and cost-efficient. You possess a strong commitment to going the extra mile and delivering projects of high quality on time. You enjoy working with others and are able to level up other engineers. Your contributions will help stakeholders to generate value from data and indirectly drive revenues.
Minimum Qualifications
5+ years of relevant experience as a data engineer.
2+ years of relevant experience as senior/staff/principal data engineer.
Excellent knowledge of Python, SQL, and Apache Spark.
Excellent knowledge of at least 1 real-time data processing framework such as Spark Streaming, Flink, or Kafka.
Demonstrated ability to design and build high-volume batch and streaming pipelines.
Demonstrated ability to design and build scalable data infrastructure.
Working experience with designing and implementing data quality checks and alerting systems.
Working experience in optimizing SQL queries in OLAP cluster (e.g. data partitioning, bucketing, z-ordering, indexing).
You are coachable. Able to own mistakes, reflect, and take feedback with maturity and a willingness to improve.
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Bachelor's degree in a technical field or equivalent work experience.
Preferred Qualifications
Working experience in developing a Python library used by internal teams. Including best practices for development and deployment.
You have a good knowledge of Terraform, CloudFormation, or other IaaC tools.
You have built data products that have scaled on AWS or another cloud.
You have experience with modern data tools such as Airflow, dbt, Kafka, Trino, Databricks, Looker, or similar.
You have experience with different databases or SQL engines and understand their trade-offs (e.g. Trino, Druid, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, etc.).
You have worked with sensitive data and ensured secure access through a data governance tool.
You have worked on building a Data platform that enables stakeholders to self-serve.
Responsibilities
Improve data pipeline logic to ensure reliability, scalability, and cost efficiency (Python, Spark, Airflow).
Ensure fast and reliable execution of analytical queries by building robust OLAP cluster (Trino, Terraform, Databricks SQL warehouse).
Design and implement a data governance policy to minimize security risks (Unity Catalog, Apache Ranger).
Own design and development of Data engineering’s internal library (Python, Spark, dbt).
Enable internal teams to build real-time applications on top of the Data lakehouse. (Spark streaming, Kafka)
Automate common data requests and unlock self-service (Retool, Flask).
Ensure high data quality through automated tests and data contracts (dbt, Great expectations).
Improve deployment process for various applications (Buddy).
Collaborate with other data engineers, analysts, and business users to design effective solutions.
Guide junior engineers and set engineering standards for the team. 
Minimize detection and recovery time from incidents and ensure the team meets important metrics and SLOs.
Research innovative technologies and integrate them into our data infrastructure.
Do whatever it takes to make Xendit succeed.

title: Cloud Engineer (Data Infrastructure)
summary:
Opswerks is seeking an experienced DevOps Engineer or individuals in a similar/comparable role. Ideal candidates will have experience providing platform or infrastructure operations support in hosted data engineering and analytics environments. Preference will be given towards experience operationalizing and optimizing Apache ecosystems such as Spark, Iceberg, and Airflow and ensuring availability and usability for developers and analysts.
Your Role
You will be part of our 24x7 team composed of talented engineers both from Opswerks and its partner-customers focusing on the development, maintenance, and operations of platforms and applications delivering quality, secure, and reliable service.
Work with our customer’s data engineering and analytics teams to support their workflows and operations running on both their in-house, indigenously developed and commercially offered platforms.
Perform root cause analysis, identify and resolve underlying problem patterns while driving automation solutions and optimizing engineering processes.
Works confidently with minimal supervision in a fast-paced, dynamic environment with a diverse group of individuals and teams.
Build tools/develop or help contribute in the improvement of solutions for challenging and business-critical problems.
Able to write clear, consumable, and effective documentation, playbooks, and other consolidated knowledge repositories that can help existing teams and future hired resources.
Design and implement end-to-end engineering solutions and processes for business opportunities
Possess leadership qualities through coaching and mentoring to improve our engineering processes and practices, quality and deliverables
Enjoys working closely with all your other talented colleagues around the world in a collaborative and respectful manner
Your Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree or higher education, preferably in computing or any related field.
Minimum of 2-3 years working in a Dev-ops environment and is well adapted to its mindset and concepts.
Minimum of 2-3 years experience with UNIX/Linux administration and is comfortable in navigating and working through the operating system environment with basic troubleshooting skills.
Working knowledge in containerization and orchestration technologies such as Docker, Kubernetes, Mesos, etc. and is very familiar with its architecture, design and operations.
Knowledgeable in the operations, design, architecture, and management of Cloud based Infrastructure preferably AWS or similar technologies like Azure, GCP
Experience with build automation, source control and CI/CD tools (GitHub, Artifactory, Jenkins, Secrets, etc)
Experience in scripting languages such as Bash, Perl and Python.
Experience in customer success and support with excellent verbal and written communication skills
Experience working on projects with cross-functional teams
The role requires an 8-hour rotating shift on a 24x7 coverage.
Amenable to a full on-site work set-up.

Plus Points
Working experience in Big Data ecosystems - Data analytics and other related operations and tools or solutions within its scope such as Apache Spark, Airflow, and Jupyter Notebook definitely is an advantage.
Adaptability and flexibility with new and emerging technologies
Relevant certifications in any of the skills on key qualifications

Who we are
Opswerks specializes in making data center and cloud operation teams thrive. Our philosophy is about making technology “Werk” for our customers by tailoring solutions to their exact needs. We believe that products, services, tools and processes should serve the needs of people, NOT the other way around.
Our global team of service architects, infrastructure admins and software engineers have built and operated some of the world’s largest, most scalable environments over the past two decades. From 24/7 monitoring to infrastructure design to application development, our team of talented, creative and dynamic people has got it all covered.
Join us at Opswerks. Together, we can make technology “Werk” for the people.
Your Team
You will be part of a diversely talented DevOps team, whose members are committed to providing quality of engineering support to opswerks' customers and their platform's users.
Our team is made up of individuals who are aligned through opswerks’ values. In the spirit of building a healthy community, which requires open and honest communication, here are our expectations for each and everyone one of us at opswerks:
To uphold opswerks’ Mission and Methods
To know, believe and execute each team’s mission plan
Growing in the 4 awarenesses (self, others, surroundings and situation)
To take ownership of your personal growth for the team’s well-being
To never give up, to never give in … only giving your best
Ready to start your awesome journey and be part of opswerks?
-

You will become the first alert, managing end-users, custom requests, and enhancement initiatives for key products in the Client Activation Analytics space. In this role you will interact frequently with leaders in Client Activation across the firm.
You will be contributing to the migration of previously build data flows in Alteryx to the new firm-approved tools (e.g., Knime, AWS Glue, Snowflake).

A degree in Industrial Engineering, Analytics, Finance, Economics or related field that combines knowledge about business processes with analytical skills
Experience with Tableau, PowerBI or similar tools is required

Experience visualizing data in different formats (dashboards, ppts, etc) and support data-driven story-telling

Entrepreneurial mindset and comfortable to test new ideas or build things from scratch

title: Senior Product Manager
summary:
Who We Are
STRATPOINT accelerates the digital transformation of businesses, delivering enterprise-grade solutions globally for more than 20 years. We specialize in agile software development, quality assurance, cloud, data engineering, and AI.
